SYMPTOM_TEXT: migraine headache for a day and a half/ felt like my head exploded; eyes were heavy; feel warm; was very unwell; had a fever; urinary tract infection; Initial information received on 17-Nov-2021 regarding an unsolicited valid non-serious case from a consumer/non-health care professional via Agency (Under reference 00861865).  This case involves a 70 years old female patient who had urinary tract infection, migraine headache for a day and a half/ felt like her head exploded (migraine), eyes were heavy (asthenopia), was very unwell (malaise), had a fever (pyrexia) and feel warm (feeling hot), after receiving INFLUENZA QUADRIVAL A-B HIGH DOSE HV VACCINE [FLUZONE HIGH-DOSE QUADRIVALENT].  The patient's past vaccination(s) included Influenza vaccine in 2018, Fluzone High Dose Quadrivalent (lot and expiration date were not reported) via unknown route in an unknown administration site for prophylactic vaccination on 07-Oct-2019 and FLUBLOK Quadrivalent (lot and expiration date were not reported) via unknown route in an unknown administration site for prophylactic vaccination on 02-OCT-2020.  Medical treatment(s), concomitant medication(s) and family history were not provided.  At the time of the event, the patient had ongoing medical history of Reaction to food additive.   On 27-Sep-2021, the patient received a dose of suspect INFLUENZA QUADRIVAL A-B HIGH DOSE HV VACCINE (lot number and expiration date were not reported) via unknown route in  an unknown administration site for prophylactic vaccination.  On 12-Nov-2021, the patient developed a non-serious urinary tract infection, 1 month 16 days (six and a half weeks) following the administration of vaccine.  On an unknown date in 2021, the patient was quite sick for three days following FLUZONE HIGH-DOSE QUADRIVALENT vaccine.   On an unknown date, the patient developed a non-serious migraine headache for a day and a half/ felt like my head exploded/ felt congested (migraine), eyes were heavy (asthenopia), was very unwell (malaise), had a fever (pyrexia) and feel warm (feeling hot) [unknown latency] following the administration of vaccine.  It was reported "I have been having problems since 2019. I received FLUZONE HIGH-DOSE on 07Oct2019, FLUBLOK on 02Oct2020, and FLUZONE HIGH-DOSE QUADRIVALENT on 27Sep2021. Then, about six and a half weeks after each of those flu vaccines, I had a urinary tract infection. I would like to know the exact ingredients in these flu vaccines and what has changed in them that may be causing me to have a urinary tract infection six and a half weeks after the vaccines. I believe something since 2019 is causing my problems. I have been consistent with getting flu shots because of my travels. In November of 2019, I got my ever first in my life urinary tract infection. My gynecologist said that I was lucky. I was almost 70 years old. I was traveling around that time, so I thought that maybe I was not drinking enough water or I was not having regular bathroom visits. Then in 2020, I was not going anywhere. I was at home and I again had a urinary tract infection in November. This year 2021, the same story. I had a urinary tract infection on 12Nov2021. It (urinary tract infection) is always six and a half weeks after I have the flu shot. Now, I am drawing a connection that it must be something from the flu shot that is causing this. It might be from something that has been added in 2019. My concern is the consistent urinary tract infection (each November). Each time I had urinalysis and it came back negative. I did not do one (urinalysis) in 2019. I did a urinalysis in 2020 and 2021 and the urinalysis came back negative. Something is giving me this urinary tract infection without any reason. This year, I was quite sick for three days following my FLUZONE HIGH-DOSE QUADRIVALENT injection on 27Sep2021. I had a migraine headache for a day and a half. I do get migraines but the headache on other side is rare and then it went behind. It was strange. On the third day, it felt like my head exploded, my eyes were heavy, and I was very unwell. The fourth strain in the FLUZONE HIGH-DOSE QUADRIVALENT may be too much for me. The fourth strain might have been responsible for the symptoms that I had. I felt like I had a fever and I felt congested, but it was all in my head. So, something is quite serious for me. I always have a reaction after a flu shot like I feel warm and do not feel so well but this time was worse. I know a lot of things have formaldehyde and that can also cause some liver problems. The pharmacy records only went back three years, so I do not know which flu vaccine I had in 2018. I will be seeing my doctor in two weeks and I would like to have information to be able to discuss with my doctor. I may try the FLUZONE STANDARD DOSE next year. Certain additives in processed foods bother me. I have a problem with MSG. I get headache or pains from it. No further information was provided."   Relevant laboratory test results included: Urine analysis in 2020 and 2021: Negative  It was not reported if the patient received a corrective treatment.  At time of reporting, the outcome was unknown for the reported events.  There will be no information available on the batch number for this case.  Follow up information was received on 22-NOV-2021 regarding an unsolicited valid non-serious case from a consumer/non-health care professional via Agency (Under reference 00861865).  Medical history and events (migraine, asthenopia, malaise, pyrexia and feeling hot) were added, corresponding fields and narrative was updated.
LAB_DATA: Test Date: 2020; Test Name: urine analysis; Test Result: Negative  ; Test Date: 2021; Test Name: urine analysis; Test Result: Negative

This spontaneous case that was received on 27-Oct-2021 from other non-healthcare professional (reference number: SEQW21-04690) and concerned a 68-year-old, female patient.  The patient's concurrent conditions included asthma. The patient's concomitant medications were not reported. The patient's historical vaccine included Fluad vaccine (unknown if trivalent or quadrivalent) after which the patient had no issues.  On 15-Oct-2021, the patient was vaccinated with Fluad Quadrivalent (influenza vaccine, inactivated influenza virus surface antigen (subunit), egg-derived, mf59; dose: 0.5 ml, anatomical location: left arm and route of administration: intramuscular) for influenza prophylaxis. The batch number reported was 312849, expiration date: 08-Jun-2022.  On the same day, right after receiving the vaccine, the patient experienced a sore arm. The patient was afraid that she received a COVID vaccine instead of a flu vaccine because the pharmacy was very busy that day and a lot of people were in the waiting room for a COVID dose.  It was confirmed that lot number provided by her, corresponded to a Fluad lot number.  On 16-Oct-2021, one day after administration of Fluad Quadrivalent, the pain worsened and started to radiate up to her neck above her left collarbone, extending to the side and back. The patient stated that the left side of her head also hurt. She also developed a deep, raspy, dry cough during this time she had never experienced before.  On 17-Oct-2021, the patient states that the symptoms began to lessen.  On 18-Oct-2021, the patient stated that most of the adverse reactions had gone away, but she did experience a sore arm, back pain and pain up the neck. The patient stated that she still had left shoulder and neck pain that extends to the top of the back, and every once in a while, she would experience a "burst" where there will be a spot on her collarbone that "sends a jolt up her neck". No corrective treatment was given for the reactions.   On the same day, the patient recovered from the events of 'headache', 'dry cough' and 'painful arm'.  On an unspecified date in Oct-2021, the patient was nervous about getting Fluad again.  The outcome of the events of 'nervous' and 'fear' was not reported.  At the time of initial reporting on 27-Oct-2021, the patient had not recovered from the events of 'shoulder pain', 'neck pain' and 'back pain'.  The reporter did not provide a causality assessment.  The reporter assessed the case as non-serious.  Company comment: One day after administration of Fluad Quadrivalent, the pain developed pain in arm, neck pain, back pain, headache and dry cough. The events are assessed as possibly related to the Fluad Quadrivalent, due to suggestive time relationship.; Sender's Comments: One day after administration of Fluad Quadrivalent, the pain developed pain in arm, neck pain, back pain, headache and dry cough. The events are assessed as possibly related to the Fluad Quadrivalent, due to suggestive time relationship.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: When the shot was administered, some of the liquid leaked out of the arm and ran down his arm to the elbow.  The immunizer  was unable to determine how much of the shot was injected. She conferred with the pharmacy manager who said that it was okay and that nothing more could be done.  The next day, I called the pharmacy and spoke to the immunizer who said that it leaked out after she took out the syringe and that at least two drops came out. She thinks that more than half went in but can't be sure. She was not sure why it happened. The following day, I called again and spoke to the manager who stated that it is too hard to estimate how many drops are in a full dose of .2mL and that generally they don't give another half shot or full shot to complete the dosage. He suggested that I could get an antibody test, but that they would not cover the cost of that expense.  He said that he was "pretty sure" that he got enough of the shot, but he was not present at the time of the administration of the shot.    I called the Health Department and the medical director stated, ?If there is a lower than authorized dose, it would be repeated. It's hard to know how much leaked out so I can't recommend if they should repeat and would defer to the person who administered. The rule of thumb had been if more than half leaked out to repeat but the new guidelines are less clear.  If I had administered and a substantial portion had leaked (even if less than half), I would repeat but I don?t have an understanding of the amount.  For example, if it?s a drop and you repeat, you would then provide a larger than authorized dose."  The patient did not experience any of the side effects that he experience after the first dose - no arm soreness, fatigue, low fever, etc.  He did have  large, circular bruise on his arm for 6 days and a puncture hole for 2 days.  This was not present after receiving the first shot.  My suspicion is that the immunizer injected him too quickly and with too much pressure, then depressed the plunger too quickly and it leaked when she pulled out.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: About 4 hours after the 2nd vaccine, I started to feel like I was getting a serious head cold and buzzy like I had taken original strength Sudafed. Over the course of the afternoon, I started to feel more lightheaded.  After work, I went to bed immediately. The next day I felt worse: worse versions of the previous day?s reactions plus a  fever ~99.0, chills, body aches and just general discomfort. Fearing these symptoms would get worse, I messaged my doctor?s office at noon (~28 hours after the vaccine) and her partner on duty that day immediately got back to me and assured me I could take tylenol to relieve those flu - like symptoms. I took 1000mg of extra strength tylenol. I felt more comfortable. The body aches stopped after a few days.  I felt out of it and fatigued for about a week. I don?t know if this is related, but 2 months (April 22, 2021) later I had a severe migraine. It was much worse than the first migraine I had 5 years before. I went to urgent care and was referred to a neurologist, who diagnosed the severe migraine a week later. Since the severe migraine in April, I have had 1 more with similar symptoms (numbness in arms and hands, etc)  in October.
HISTORY: JuvEnile rheumatoid arthritis in remission since age 20. I had 1 migraine in my life before the vaccine.
ALLERGIES: Medication: Relafen, (and my allergist told me never to take ibuprophen) Foods: Chicken, wheat, soy, pea, lobster, oyster,  oat, flax seed, fish, egg white, salmon, tuna, tomato,  Other allergies: grass, dust, cat pelt and dander, trees (multiple), feathers, ragweed

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Booster shot administered around 11:45 am 01Dec2021.  Onset of headache by 4 pm 01Dec2021. Headache continued through 18:00 on 02Dec2021 (ibuprofen used to manage pain). Consistent aching pain/discomfort (~7 on a 1-10 scale) with occasional sharp spikes. Difficulty lifting/moving arm. Lymph node can easily be located and is very firm. Pain/swelling persists as of this report.  Red rash/hives on neck observed around 8 am 03Dec2021. Worsened and spread to chest throughout the day. Itchy and hot. Benadryl used to manage itch. The rash was 95% cleared by 8:30 am 04Dec2021.  I experienced all three of the above reactions after my second dose as well, so they were not entirely unexpected. I am reporting for informational purposes. If my lymph node swelling does not go down in a week I will follow up with a doctor.
OTHER_MEDS: Oral birth control,  B12, and multivitamin
PRIOR_VAX: Moderna COVID vaccine dose 2, lot 025C21A. Same symptoms as current event

I had been having breathing troubles since mid March, but since I am being evaulated every three months for recurrence of cancer, did not think too much about it. The shortness of breath has gradually gotten worse with even mild exertion . On November 25, I began to feel the symptoms of a common cold; sore and scratchy throat, fever, headache, sweats, labored breathing (worse than usual). By Nov 28, I felt like I might have had breakthrough COVID, so I submitted a PCR at pharmacy. That night, symptoms worsened, so I went to Urgent Care. A chest X-Ray and swab for pneumonia were taken, and both were negative. I was sent home with no medications and told to return if worse. On Nov. 29, I felt considerable worse, to the point that I called 911 for fear I would pass out driving. I could not catch my breath and my oxygen sats on my home oximeter were in the mid 80's. An EKG was obtained and I heard the paramedi state it was suspicious. I was taken to the hospital, and had a CT, bloodwork, breathing treatment and oxygen administered. I was sent home with Steroids, and a diagnosis of rhino enterovirus. The discharge summary states that I was in acute respiratory distress.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: My immune system is not protecting me from infections or allergies, see continuation page I have a history of low IGG values. Back in 2020, my Immunoglobulin G was 550 mg/dL. My IG A was 70 mg/dL. Back in 1996 they performed a bone biopsy, to prove this was genetic.   After getting the booster of J&J, batch 213D21A on Oct 29.2021, I had no symptoms for one week and then I started to get symptoms which I normally get when I am fighting a cold or a worsening of my Celiac disease. The difference, which wasn't apparent at first, was I'm not clearing them. I will go into detail for each:  Two major items are my allergies are not controllable and I'm being attacked by fungus.  1) Fungus infections are not clearing a. On Nov 17 I got Athlete's Foot. In the past I would catch this if I walked in mud in my back yard by the lake. As soon as my feet would start peeling, I would use a tube of Terbinafine cream and a week later they would be better. This time, I did nothing to cause it, and it is not clearing and in fact spreading. It is 2 � weeks now.   b. On Nov 14th I pulled a few hairs from inside my nose, and they got infected, in the past I put Bacitracin on it and expected it would be healed in 2 days, but on Nov 16th it developed into a fungus infection and had an awful smell. I started treating it with Nystatin and Triamcinolone and 2 � weeks later I still have the infection. It still smells if I touch it. c. Around Nov 10th hairs on my chest, back and crotch were hurting. I tried to shave them off and each hair got red and hurt worse. I have been rubbing Nystatin and Triamcinolone on them twice daily since. Never has this gone on more than two days.   2) Pollen Allergies are the worst I have ever had a. I take Flonase 50 mcg twice daily and was also taking Astelin 131 mcg. I was having problems urinating and was wetting my pants and dripping on the floor. I haven't had these issues since I had prostate surgery 15 years ago. Back then I had an obstruction, and any antihistamine would keep me from urinating, as it is a muscle relaxer. So, about 9 months ago I started to use Astelin to clear a sinus infection and keep on taking it. Well, I stopped it on Nov 22nd and the voiding problem disappeared, but now I am now so sensitive to pollen, it is troubling. My eyes are itching, and I can't run a meeting for work without sucking on a Halls drop, because I'm constantly congested. This is not allergy season and if my wife brings home flowers I start sneezing if I get near them. If it is windy or raining, I get so congested I get headaches. When I blow my nose, I get some blood out, in it.  I've been running our home AC fan to filter out her pollen, but it isn't helping. In the 28 years I lived here I have never experienced these problems. 3) Body strain a. When I lay in bed watching TV, or when I wake up in the morning, I can't lean forward, as it really hurts. In fact, if I must sneeze, I scream out and it causes a sharp pain in my lower back. This strain I had for the past three years as our mattress wore out, but I replaced it with a firm, latex mattress back in July. But in the past three weeks the strain is back and stronger. b. Certain muscles to my left arm really hurt for no reason, randomly. I never had that pain before 4) Mouth Infections a. Around Nov 5th, I thought I had a canker sore and treated it with Hydrogen Peroxide 4%, but it didn't clear in the 7 days it normally takes. It may be gone today, but I have another infection on the other side which is still there. I never had anything like this which lasted more than one week.  What I'm so concerned about is it appears to me that my immune system is not working, or it is busy. Medicines are not working, and I am getting worse. I'm getting more fatigued, for no reason. I'm fearing this is Antiboby-Dependent Enhancement (ADE). I want to know if this is from the J&J booster and if at some point my immune system will recover, or do I have to be super careful to avoid any infections as they will kill me?  I think I should never get another booster for Covid-19.
OTHER_MEDS: Crestor, Nexium, Flonase, Astelin, Centrim Adult, Topicort, Nystatin & Triamcinolone
ALLERGIES: Propylene Glycol, Gluten, Cefzil, Sulfa, Pollen, Orange, Sorghum, Latex, blue cheese, sulfites, jalapenos

I felt better sitting up.  The next day I went to the doctor,  they put me in the hospital. That was a Sunday when I went in and I was released on Thursday. They gave me  Colchicine. And I basically had a lot of pain. Every breath hurt. I could breathe but it hurt.  For a couple of days,  I had sharp pains, it took a few months that I did not have that pain when I would breathe but it got better.  It seemed to have flared  up  inflammation in the lining around the heart, lining around the lungs, ribs, breast bones, my shoulders, and the my neck. Everything got inflamed in my upper body. That happened while I was in the hospital on Sunday, Monday and Tuesday and by Thursday it calmed down.

I reported my symptoms to her , but called Dr to see what he would want me to do.  His nurse suggested that I go to the ER right the.  I did and was diagnosed with blood clots in my lungs. EXTREME loss of breath happens when I really exert myself physically such as climbing stair.   I DID NOT HAVE THIS CONDITION BEFORE I GOT MY MODERNA BOOSTER! I am pro Vaccination but I repeat I did not have this condition before I received the Moderna booster. The CDC says that have one case of something like this so far. I wonder how many other people are out there they may have milder blood clots than mine and are just say, not feeling well.  And the hospital said my heart was fine, blood gases normal and blood work also. Please feel free to contact them for my results!!

Patient received an additional dose (third dose, 0.5mL) of the Moderna COVID vaccine on Tuesday, 11/30/21. Pt is immunocompromised and was instructed to receive a full dose per doctor. We administered the correct dose. During the 15-minute waiting period (post-vaccine), pt began feeling dizzy, light-headed, and experienced a racing heartbeat. When the 15 minute observation period was over, the RPh was on the phone and not available for consultation right away. Pt did not want to wait and informed the cashier of her side effects, then she went home directly. Pt asked for the RPh to call her as soon as she got a chance. Pt reported the adverse reaction to her doctor and also to the pharmacy manager between 11/30-12/2. Pt attempted to reach RPh, but pharmacy was short staffed and told the pt we would call her back. Pt never received a phone call from the pharmacy until Friday, 12/3 when the adverse vaccine reaction was communicated to a different RPh. This other RPh called the pt on 12/3, obtained details of reaction, submitted an internal vaccine incident report with Costco, and also submitted a VAERS report.  Between Tues. 11/30/21 and Fri. 12/3/21, pt began to experience more adverse effects, and the reaction to the vaccine progressed and worsened. On 11/30 (evening), pt began experiencing normal vaccine side effects about 4-6 hours post-vaccine. Pt reported these side effects: fever, painful arm (so sore she could not move it), fatigue, nausea, muscle pain. Over the course of the next couple days (between 11/30-12/3), pt continued to experience a fever and developed further adverse effects. Pt reported abdominal pain, joint pain, bright red & swollen fingers, bright red & swollen knees, bruises on both hands (with no injuries), and extreme fatigue. Fever peaked at 102 degrees F. Pt has been taking Tylenol around-the-clock since 12/1 to control fever; currently no fever on 12/3 while taking Tylenol. Pt was seen by her PCP on Fri. 12/3. Per report from pt's doctor, the adverse vaccine reaction appears to be an arthritic reaction and presents like Raynaud's syndrome. Pt was given a double dose of steroid injection (IM) in the doctor's office on 12/3, and she was also prescribed short term prednisone tx. Pt is being referred to a rheumatoid arthritis specialist for further tests and ongoing medical care.
LAB_DATA: No tests or labs performed on 12/3/21 during doctor visit. Patient has been referred to a rheumatoid arthritis specialist for further tests and evaluation to determine underlying cause for this vaccine reaction.
OTHER_MEDS: 1) cephalexin 500mg, 1 cap twice daily for 7 days (started on 11/29/21) 2) indomethacin 50mg 3) buspirone 5mg 4) albuterol sulfate 0.083% nebulizer solution, PRN only 5) bupropion XL 150mg 6) Epi-Pen 0.3mg, PRN only
CUR_ILL: Pt does have SVT (supraventricular tachycardia). Other health conditions are unknown. Pharmacy staff submitted this report on behalf of the patient, per patient request.

The next morning after the vaccine I woke up extremely stiff. My back was in excruciating pain and anytime I tried to move the pain was so severe it was at crying level. EMT was called because my husband couldn't get me into the car for transport. I was transported to ER and was diagnosed that the disc in my back from L3 to S1  had completely swollen applying pressure on all the nerves and muscles in my back. I was treated with morphine and several steroid shots and was monitored until I could finally sit up and was released. I visited my PCP the next day and by that time I could walk on a walker and he again gave more steroid shots to help elevate the swelling. This persisted for about a week where I had a hard time walking and was still taking the steroid pills to help make the additional swelling go down. The early part of the summer I was beginning to develop various red spots all over my body. My dermatologist stated something upset my whole immune system and diagnosed me with Sudden Onset Psoriasis. I have never, nor does my family have a history of Psoriasis so she attributed it back to the COVID vaccine as well because nothing else had changed to make this occur. My Dermatologist stated this is now a chronic issue and will never go away and I have to use an expensive cream to help treat for the rest of my life and she also has advised Phototherapy where I will be treated with pills and shots the remainder of my life and to date I am still seeing a Physical Therapist as well for my back.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I began experiencing vertigo on around 3/2/2021 at about 10:30PM. As I lay in my bed, whenever I moved my head, the room began spinning. The room also spun whenever I tried to get up from my bed. The dizziness was so bad my husband gave me a walker, because I was unable to move around without holding onto something. The vertigo got progressively worse every day until finally on 3/12/2021, I couldn't stop vomiting. I had to go to the ER at a local healthcare center. I was given Zofran to treat the vomiting and prescribed meclizine to treat the vertigo. I underwent bloodwork, a COVID-19 test, and a chest X-ray. I tested negative for COVID-19, and the bloodwork indicated my neutrophils were very elevated. No abnormalities were detected in the chest X-ray. The vertigo got progressively better each day afterwards. By the time I got my second Moderna injection on 3/26/2021, the vertigo was gone. When I got my second dose of Moderna, I didn't have a recurrence of vertigo.
LAB_DATA: When I went to the ER at a local medical center, I underwent bloodwork, a chest X-ray, and a COVID-19 test. I tested negative for COVID-19 and had elevated neutrophil levels. No abnormalities were detected in the X-ray.
OTHER_MEDS: Ambien; Crestor; Flovent HFA; Multivitamins; Vitamin C; Vitamin D3; Vitamin E; Osteo Bi-Flex; Quercetin; Zinc; Magnesium.
PRIOR_VAX: I had a negative reaction with the first double dose of flu vaccine.

I discussed with pharmacy and together we have not heard of this is a side effect of the Pfizer vaccine though we will certainly write it up and send it and should this become a problem with this very new therapy. I do not think he needs emergent imaging now given that his pain is nearly completely resolved and his neurological exam is normal.  We talked about warning signs such as tingling weakness facial droop as signs to come back emergently for further work-up. They will also come back if his pain gets more severe. Immediately upon receiving the vaccination, I felt like something wasnt right.  I was not held for any amount of time at PHARMACY to see if i would react, I was released directly after receiving the shot.  I first felt dizzy, like my vision was blurred, hot flashes, and headed straight home.   Upon entering my house I Felt as if I were freezing, went to the couch, and went to very strong chills, more like convulsions for a couple of hours until I finally went to sleep.  During this time I was very delerious.  The chills and pain continued throughout the night, and then i begin vomiting,  I couldnt keep water down.  I finally became dehydrated and couldn't handle it anymore Friday morning and went to the ER.  I was delirous throughout this time off and on, the highest I noticed my fever before taking Tylenol was 100.7.  I would start shaking at 98.5, convulsion like chills at 99.5.  The ER admitted me and diagnosed as Dehydration.  The administered 2 liters of fluids, diagnosed a UTI, administered an antibiotic through the IV, and also gave Zofran, as I threw up at registration and again in triage.  After I was released, The fever stopped 11/23/21.  I continued taking Zofran to be able to eat and keep some food down.  12/2/2021 I was able to drive a little again, but as of today, I am still weak, have absolutely no urge to eat, have to force myself.  My joints and bones are hurting, but I am able to stay hydrated.  I will not be taking any further vaccinations due to the response to the first one.
LAB_DATA: Lab work was done when I went to the ER on the 19th of November.

Vaccination clinic was done which included pediatric doses and adult booster doses. I was notified by the volunteer vaccinator nurse that the patient requested Moderna COVID-vaccine for her booster dose but was given Pfizer Pediatric dose.  Pt received 0.2mL of Pfizer pediatrics. Local county health department was contacted and consulted (Nurse coordinator) and she advised how to proceed. She said that it is best to ask the patient to be given 2/3 of the amount of Pfizer adult booster dose since a pediatric dose is 1/3 of an adult dose. This way, patient will still complete the necessary dose for the adult booster. Mixing vaccines is now an option (e.g. If patient had Moderna for primary series, patient can now get Pfizer as booster).  The patient came back to the vaccination clinic and was given a 2nd vaccination the same day of Pfizer adult dose 0.2 ml. These are the vaccines that the patient received: Pfizer 10mcg/0.2ml = 0.2 ml and Pfizer 30mcg/0.3ml = 0.2 ml. Total dose received for the day is 30mcg.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient received the vaccination per protocol in the pharmacy. After approximately 15 minutes she approached the pharmacist indicating she felt a little dizzy and scratchy in her throat. I asked some follow-up questions to assess possible causes for the dizziness. I then provided 25 mg liquid diphenhydramine for the patient, which she promptly took. After about 10 minutes I reassessed the patient and she said that the scratchiness was persisting and I provided another 25 mg of liquid diphenhydramine. The patient rested in the pharmacy waiting area while waiting for the medication to take effect. She was reassessed every 5 minutes to determine  how she was progressing. At first she started to feel better, but subsequently after about 25 minutes she indicated that she felt some swelling in her face and throat. I further examined her and didn't notice any frank swelling of the tongue. I advised them they could proceed to emergency to be treated for an allergy there or they could go to urgent care for treatment with possible steroids or other medication. The patient and her husband then left the pharmacy and headed for more medical attention.

on 11/19/2021 received vaccine at 1pm.  At 10pm on 11/19/2021 experienced minor headache and chills and went to bed.  At 2am on 11/20/2021 I woke with worsening headache on the left side, chills and nausea then went back to sleep.  Waking at 10am there was a severe headache on the left side, blurry vision in left eye, pain in left eye and nausea.  Took Tylenol 650mg without effect.  Returned to bed and woke at 2pm, eye pain, headache and nausea continued and I called my doctor.  Doctor advised to go to emergency room for evaluation.  Arrived at Hospital in at approximately 3pm  CAT scan of head, multiple MRIs of brain and labs were completed and all within normal limits.  Neurologist was consulted, no neurological deficits were noted.  Ophthomalogy consult identified increase in eye pressure in left eye and possible angle closure to left eye and loss of functional vision in the left eye.  Eye medications started along with oral medications which lowered eye pressure and released home 6pm on Sunday 11/21/2021.  Ophthamologist recommended eye clinic for further evaluation.  Monday, 11/22/2021 went to emergency room.  Pain had subsided in left eye yet still no functional vision.   Diagnosed acute angle closure in left eye and glaucoma in both eyes, and a cataract in the left eye.  Recommended to continue eye drop medications as prescribed by RWJ and referred Hospital glaucoma clinic for treatment.  Performed laser treatment on left eye on 11/24/2021 and laser treatment on right eye on 11/26/2021.  Further recommended cataract removal and lens implant on left eye to be performed within 2-3 months.  Vision in left eye is currently improving and pain has subsided.
LAB_DATA: 11/20/2021: blood work, CAT scan and MRIs, found nothing abnormal 11/21/2021: ophthalmology noted increased pressure in eyes and recommended follow up at clinic
OTHER_MEDS: Xarelto 10mg daily multi-vitamin daily baby aspirin 81mg daily glucosamine daily chondroitin daily

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Symptoms Before Adverse Event: Pain on injection site (left arm) which started a few minutes after injection and got worse for the next 24 hours (later began subsiding after around 36 hours of injection). Fever (102 degrees Fahrenheit) and chills the night after receiving the vaccine (lasted around 6 to 8 hours). I had difficulty sleeping that night. I was uncomfortable and had muscle aches everywhere. I felt dehydrated and  got hungry in the middle of the night so I drank some water and ate two small bowls of Mac and Cheese before taking two tablets of 650mg Tylenol (to lower the fever because it was getting gradually getting higher). The following morning after waking up (I only slept for a few hours), I was sweating (fever was gone) and I got up to go to the bathroom. This is when the "adverse event" began.  Adverse Event: As I was standing in the bathroom getting ready to urinate, I started feeling a dizzy and my heart was pounding harder than usual (not faster or slower, but stronger beats). My vision got blurry and I started seeing white stars (white filling up my vision). I then felt this odd hollow, nauseating feeling in my stomach and began feeling too weak to properly focus. I started walking out of the bathroom to call for help and was helped to lay down on a bed. I felt like I was fainting (I have never fainted before but I am pretty certain that must be what it feels like to start to lose consciousness and the ability to move as you begin fainting).  Treatment and Outcome: As I was laying down, I fortunately started feeling like my energy was returning. My vision began reappearing and despite feeling extremely anxious during this incident, I was now feeling a bit more calm as it felt like I was getting better now. My parents where in the process of getting a phone to call ED to get help for the emergency but put that on hold as they helped me sit. I was not sure what had just happened and if I should go to the emergency room. I felt weak, scared, and kept grabbing my chest (I felt like I needed to feel my pulse and breathe deeply). I used Agency to call a doctor for advise on what to do. She mentioned that she believes that I had Orthostatic Hypotension as a result of the vaccine-related fever, being dehydrated, and getting up quickly. She told me that if I continued to feel sick then to go see a doctor in person but she said I didn't have to go to the emergency room now unless I felt like I had to or the incident reoccurs. At 11:40am this morning patient received her Pfizer booster vaccine by pharmacist. Pharmacist worked through the patient's immunization questionnaire form, noting no contraindication to the vaccine nor any past history of adverse effects to prior immunizations. The report form was provided to patient and it was explained that patient was welcomed to wait 15 minutes post immunization at our designated observation area, which she agreed to do. Two to three minutes after Patient began her 15-minute post immunization observation patient fainted, falling to the floor from her seated position. Patient's husband was with her during this time. A pharmacy customer who witnessed the incident immediately notified myself of the situation and I immediately went out to assist. My initial observation of the situation was the patient already lying on the floor unconscious, cyanotic, and had a slight lip cut on her lower lip. Patient's husband began raising the patient legs up while he began explaining to me that the patient had indeed had previous fainting incidents in past immunizations and that this was not her first time. Within a few seconds the patient regained consciousness and the husband began trying to have her sit up. I explained to the husband that it was best that the patient remained on the floor lying down till she was stable. Patient became unconscious again and seemed as though she was about to seize so I positioned her on her side. No seizure was actually observed and patient regained consciousness again after about 10 seconds. I instructed that the patient remain on her side till she was stable. At this time store management was onsite taking notes and offering that we call an ambulance, for which both patient and husband declined. An ice pack was placed on the patients back and she remained laying down for another 10 minutes till stabilized. Patient was alert and orientated to person, place, and time and showed proper neurological and muscular function by being able to squeeze both of my hands. I sat her up and provided an orange juice for her to sip on while I had her wait in the observation area for another 30 minutes to ensure she was okay. After 30 minutes, Patient indicated she felt much better and left the store with her husband and children. I followed up with the patient this afternoon at 7:45pm to check in on her. Patient confirmed that she felt fine and was very appreciative for all that we did for her.
PRIOR_VAX: Pfizer--fainted, 43 yrs

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Fever, worsening cough, chills, extreme fatigue and muscle pain for over 7 days. Returned to work after missing 9 days due to vaccine side effects, but cough and fatigue continued until August 6,2021 when we finally went to hospital ER with what we thought was bronchitis our maybe pneumonia. However, we were devastated when they diagnosed him with Stage C congestive heart failure! This was out of the blue. Other than a persistent mild cough which we thought was from smoking, he was healthy, normal weight, active and had no idea his heart was in danger. I watched him go from healthy to a man who was scared and dying over the course of a few weeks following his second vaccine dose. I don't care what conclusion is made, because I will always blame the vaccine. I saw it with my own eyes. Correlation isn't causation, but it would have to be one hell of a coincidence if the vaccine didn't trigger SOMETHING. His cardiologist dismissed my concerns over this, which is very disconcerting, and we have a new cardiologist that we can't see until February. Someone should document his case.

Hi  -    Pt had her second covid vaccine shot yesterday morning around 10am. By 9pm she was slightly fevery, very fatigued, and her eyes were rather red. She said she was exhausted and went to bed. At 4am she came to our room, seemingly fully awake but talking nonsensically (said "but does 4 x 78 work??" several times, talked about her "coloring books" and then eventually said "I just can't do it. Can I just forget about my numbers and snuggle while I fall asleep?"). Needless to say it was rather disturbing. We've never had anything like this with her before. We let her sleep in this morning and when she woke up at 9am, she was again disoriented (looked at my husband and me after she had been awake for a couple of minutes and asked "but which one is the real mother?"). She didn't seem particularly scared or disturbed, just really out of it. She ate some breakfast and while she is sort of quiet now and complaining only of feeling a little nauseous, she no longer seems disoriented. That said, she's not totally herself. She hasn't asked about school at all which is very unlike her.     I'm mostly just letting you know for reference sake. I trust she will be totally fine in hopefully short order, but this was an unexpected and pretty concerning side effect.     Have you heard of anything like this with this vaccine or any others?    Thanks so much,     Addendum: Pt ended up going to school on this day, but also had a fever of 103F later in the day.

After receiving the COVID 19 vaccine (which was mandated as a military member),  within 24 hours I felt extreme fatigue.  By Tuesday early morning I had began having severe coughing fits that were dry and uncontrollable. I was also short of breath both while moving (going up a flight of stairs) and while sedentary at times and had instances where my heart felt like it was fluttering. My chest/lungs felt like a small child was sitting on them aside from the burning, raspy cough.  I took several cough suppressants to minimize the symptoms but as the coughing fits were keeping me up at night I went to my primary care physician on 10/5/2021. The nurse practitioner and I went over my symptoms and I was diagnosed with severe bronchial spasms with the potential for an asthma diagnosis. Having no issues with breathing previously, I asked that we rule other things out like bronchitis or an infection. The coughing fits continued with cough suppressants not minimizing the symptoms. I was told if I had an upper respiratory infection there was not much that could be done and that I should return in 6-8 weeks if the symptoms persist. On 11/2/2021 I received the second dose of the vaccine (again due to the military mandate and my unit's deadline of being fully vaccinated by 12/2/2021), and experienced the same extreme fatigue. At this point, the symptoms still had not subsided so I scheduled another appointment for 11/19/2021. The nurse practitioner indicated that it could still be an upper respiratory infection, perhaps indigestion (with zero previous issues with indigestion), or if I was not better in a month that we needed to seriously consider asthma and that based on the timing of my symptoms it appeared that the vaccine was the culprit as I had exhibited none of the symptoms prior to these events. I was prescribed an albuterol inhaler to aid in the coughing fits and shortness of breath. We scheduled a follow up visit for mid January to complete the diagnosis. As of 12/5/2021 I still have the symptoms described above. I remain short of breath and even long conversations often put me out of breath despite being previously moderately healthy and fit- per military requirements. The cold air exacerbates the coughing fits.

Background: about 2 years ago, it turns out I had a bilateral deep vein thrombosis blood clot in both lungs. It manifested by a very sharp muscle pain, to the left side of my back. I attributed it to be a muscle strain, however the next day I became very weak. I found myself to have difficulty exerting myself in any degree whatsoever. I happened to pick up an oximeter. I was playing with it that night and it read 85. That night I went to be ER. I was given a blood thinner, Eliquis, and was released the next day. I went off the blood thinners after 6 months. I was diagnosed with DPE/dual pulmonary embolism. I was put on Eliquis on 03/04/2018. The source of the blood clot was my left leg. I was taken off the Eliquis 09/2018. On 03/05/2021 about 9 hours later after the vaccine, I started to have that very sharp pain in my back. The exact same place I felt it 3 years prior of the vaccine. The oximeter was down to 90. I decided to hang tough before I went to the ER. Within 2 hours the pain had gone away the oximeter went up to 96. At 8:00PM on Friday the pain had gone away and the oxygen level was back to normal. On Monday, I called my PCP and I asked him to prescribe blood thinner and I restarted the Eliquis bd on Monday. I continued that until I got my 2nd dose on 03/26/2021. I did not have the symptoms I had after the 1st dose. I had the booster 10/01/2021. I also started Eliquis 2 weeks before the dose, and I did not have the same reaction as the 1st dose. I honestly do not know if I would have had the same reaction with the booster, but I was not going to take the chance.
OTHER_MEDS: Tamsulosin 0.4 mg bd Lisinopril 10 mg od Fenofibrate 160 mg od Vitamin 81 mg Aspirin 1000 mg salmon oil Niacin

I listed all three COVID-19 vaccines I've had to date.  About 6 to 8 weeks after my 2nd Pfizer vaccine I began experiencing Tinnitus in both ears... No clue if the vaccines have anything to do with this but I've never had Tinnitus before and have not had an experience that would knowingly cause this condition. I was watching the news one night and there was a report about some people experiencing tinnitus, wondering if it "might be" related to COVID vaccines or COVID-19 itself. To my knowledge, I've never had COVID-19. My jaw dropped and I felt I should report this... if we don't look into possible side effects, and report ANYTHING different about our bodies before we had the vaccines, how will scientists ever know what's happening.  I did have some ear wax removed from one ear after my hearing became muffled and that helped my left ear and my hearing but the Tinnitus remains in both ears... and honestly.. after my Moderna booster on 11/9/2021... I'm noticing it's getting increasingly more intense. I plan on going to either a hearing doctor and/or ENT to get checked out further. Don't know if this is related to the vaccines or the disease but I'm all for Vaccines and would just like to know if they may have caused this condition. I can live with it but it's a mystery that did not occur until after a couple of Covid vaccines.
LAB_DATA: On 7/29/2021 I visited Doctor at Clinic after hearing in my left ear became muffled. The Nurse did some wax removal which restored my hearing in that left ear.. I also told them I had been experiencing tinnitus in both ears since June 2021. Did not know at the time there were some other reports of folks with Tinnitus, wondering if there could possibly be a link to the COVID-19 vaccines. My hearing seems fine but this Tinnitus started about 6-8 weeks after my 2nd Pfizer vaccine and now after my booster on 11/9/21, the tinnitus has increased significantly. Again, no clue if this is related to the vaccines, or just stress, age or other factors.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 9/1/2021: Entyvio infusion in the morning, 9:30 am. First Pfizer dose in the afternoon, 3:00 pm - lot number FF2588. Virtually no reaction at all to the Pfizer first dose - no sickness, no drowsiness, nothing - felt fine. Suspected that Entyvio blocked Pfizer reaction.  Around 9/18/2021: Started having very mild hives and itching. Did not suspect the vaccine at this time.  9/22/2021: Second Pfizer dose in the afternoon - lot number FE3592. No immediate reaction.  9/23/2021: 24 hours after second dose, face and hands break out into significant hives and swelling (almost couldn?t get my rings off my fingers).  9/23 through 10/17/2021: Near daily severe hives, almost all over my body with varying severity depending on location that changed location daily - some days my face was worst, some my legs and feet, some my back and chest and shoulders, some my hands, some my head and neck, etc. Severe itching. Throat itching, difficulty/strange feeling swallowing, feeling of heart burn. Sweaty feet. Swelling in face, throat, hands, and feet varied daily. Got first pack of steroids on 9/25 (methylprednisolone), then progressively got stronger steroids (Prednisone then Dexamethasone) before finally getting some relief starting about 9/30. Stayed on steroids and antihistamine (mostly Benadryl) until symptoms abated enough to stop, which wasn?t until about 10/17/2021. Severity of hives and swelling nearly resulted in going to the ER several times, even after getting on steroids.  10/17/2021+: Symptoms mostly gone, with some odd days showing recurrence of mild hives and itching. Sweaty/clammy feet still persist, though not as intensely.  10/27/2021: Another Entyvio infusion. Vaccine reaction symptoms abated significantly after this infusion. Again, it is expect that the Entyvio is reducing the vaccine reaction.  11/27/2021: Mild symptoms are returning, suspected to be due to Entyvio concentration waning in my system. Experiencing strangeness in swallowing, mild itching, very mild hives, sweaty feet.  12/5/2021: Mild symptoms persist and are getting progressively, though very slightly, more intense. Itching, mild hives, throat/swallowing strangeness, and sweaty feet are still the primary complaints. Reporting on VAERS.
LAB_DATA: Labs were ordered by my primary physician, but I never got the blood work done.
OTHER_MEDS: ENTYVIO (vedolizumab) infusions every 8 weeks for Crohn's disease.

patient received 2 vaccines today. Fluzone HD and Moderna booster dose. 83 year old patient was with his adult daughter (she takes care of him) and she brought him in to get vaccinated. He was screened by pharmacist and vaccines administered by pharmacy tech. He was informed during screening about the requirement to wait for 15 minutes in wait area. After vaccines had been administered the daughter said that her Dad needed to go to bathroom and she was going to take him. A few minutes later an associate said someone needed assistance up front at the bathrooms. When I (pharmacist) got up front, I saw that it was the patient (83 yo) that we had vaccinated a few minutes earlier. He and his daughter were in front of bathrooms up front. She said he tried to stand up to go to bathroom and his face went blank and his eyes rolled back in his head. She got him back in the wheel chair that he uses. The patient was somewhat responsive, breathing, sweating and cool to touch. He did have a pulse. We applied cool compresses, but he seemed to not be getting betting after a couple of minutes, so I had the front end assistant call emergency services. I tried to get a blood pressure reading but patient had on sweatshirt and heavy jacket. We removed the jacket and were about to get a blood pressure reading when EMS arrived. They got patient history from daughter and I informed them of the 2 vaccines administered to him. They transported patient to hospital. This happened about 3:25 pm today. I called the daughter a few minutes ago to check on the patient. The doctors told her that he did NOT suffer a stroke or heart attack. They were running bloodwork and she stated they would probably release him this evening.
LAB_DATA: THE EXACT TESTS/LAB RESULTS FROM THE HOSPITAL THE PATIENT WAS TRANSPORTED TO ARE UNKNOWN AT THIS TIME.
OTHER_MEDS: UNKNOWN, PATIENT ONLY CAME TO US TO GET VACCINATED. FLUZONE HD AND MODERNA BOOSTER
HISTORY: DAUGHTER STATES PATIENT HAS HAD A HEART ATTACK IN THE PAST

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Exactly 7 days after vaccination (almost to the hour), she complained of stomach/intestinal distress. She failed to eat dinner and went to sleep at dinner time. She awoke multiple times during the night in distress, from what seemed like post-nasal drip at the time (though it's hard to tell in a 5-year-old). The next morning, she had a low-grade fever (99.6). She was in good spirits and was able to go to school (per the school's policy), but was later described by her teacher as being out of sorts and "not herself". She improved throughout the day and, though fatigued, her temperature returned to normal by the following day. We assumed it was a cold, but this evening (12 days after the vaccine, and several days after recovering from the symptoms described above) she complained of pain in her leg (left leg I think), almost to the point of tears. She wanted to go to sleep early (5:00pm) instead of eat dinner again. We gave her children's ibuprofen before she fell asleep. Her temperature is currently normal and, to our knowledge, her current symptoms are only fatigue and pain in her leg. She is sleeping now.   Between the initial symptoms and today, she also had green poop for multiple days and restless sleep (waking or crying out nearly every hour) for two additional nights after the first night.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: COVID BREAKTHROUGH  Pfizer Dose 1 2/10/21 (EN6201) Pfizer Dose 2 3/3/21 (EN6199) COVID Positive 8/22/21  8/22/21: Patient is a 75 year old male with past history of coronary disease status post CABG, ischemic cardiomyopathy status post AICD placement, diabetes mellitus, hypertension, and hyperlipidemia who was admitted after having multiple shocks from his AICD.  History is obtained from chart review as well as discussion with the patient and the ED provider.  Patient does have a history of a coronary artery bypass in 1990.  He has a history of multiple stents and appears his last stents were placed approximately 2 years ago at an outside hospital.  Last stents placed at this hospital were an 2016. He does still take aspirin and Plavix daily.  Patient states that he was driving yesterday morning when he rear-ended a vehicle at approximately 12:30 a.m..  He states that the airbags did deploy a and that he had significant pain on his chest from the seatbelt.  He denies losing consciousness prior to the episode.  He did not seek out medical treatment at that time and went home.  He went to sleep and then woke up to after being shocked by his defibrillator.  He thought he was shocked about 3 times however on interrogation he received a total of 10 shocks and a 5 minutes period.  His chest is quite sore and overall just feels weak from the defibrillator episodes.  Not having any current shortness of breath, fevers, chills, nausea, vomiting, abdominal pain.  Transferred to this hospital after being started on amiodarone infusion.  Troponin slightly elevated.  9/3/21: Patient was admitted and Cardiology was consulted given AICD firing for ventricular fibrillation.  Was recommended that he undergo an ischemic workup however he is COVID-19 test returned positive.  He was started on remdesivir as well as Decadron.  He did have some mild hypoxemia.  He was placed on a heparin infusion as well as amiodarone infusion.  He was switched to oral amiodarone and underwent coronary angiogram on 8/27.  He had a drug-eluting stent placed to the saphenous vein graft to the obtuse marginal branch.  Patient was going to be discharged the following day however did develop some hypoxemia.  Hypoxemia worsened and on 08/29 he under went a PA cardiac arrest.  He did have some ventricular fibrillation and ROSC was obtained.  He was transferred to the ICU.  Pulmonary was consulted and he underwent hypothermia protocol.  His neurologic status was quite poor however sedation was not able to be weaned given his significant hypoxemia related to COVID-19.  He was started on broad-spectrum antibiotics.  Family ultimately decided on comfort measures given his poor prognosis from a heart standpoint, respiratory failure, and suspected anoxic brain injury.  He was palliatively extubated and passed away at 1:02 p.m. on 09/03/2021.

COVID Breakthrough  Pfizer Dose 1 4/15/21 (Er8732) Pfizer Dose 2 5/21/21 (EW0168) COVID Positive 8/25/21  8/25/21: Patient is a 55 year old female with a history of COPD, pulmonary embolism on anticoagulation, HTN, tobacco abuse, sickle-cell anemia who presents for evaluation of shortness of breath.   Patient notes that she started feeling sick on Monday. She initially presented to clinic on Monday for evaluation. Patient's primary symptom is shortness of breath.  She notes that going upstairs she has more difficulty than normal.  Patient has also had increased cough productive of white/yellow sputum.  Patient notes that she has had some right sided rib pain, but is currently denying chest pain. She denied recent sick contacts or exposure to COVID. Patient is not vaccinated for COVID.  No hemoptysis, recent travel or calf tenderness.  Patient notes she had a left rotator cuff surgery recently.  No other concerns today. In the emergency department patient's vitals showed tachycardia to 111.   Patient's initial oxygen saturation was 82% on room air, but improved into the mid 90s on 4 L. labs were obtained and showed mild transaminitis, lactic acid 4.0, troponin 0.01.  ABG showed pH 7.36, pCO2 34, HC03 19. Blood cultures X 2 ordered.  COVID rapid antigen positive.  Chest x-ray showed evidence heart failure with small bilateral pleural effusions and moderate pulmonary vascular congestion as well as airspace disease in the bilateral lower lobes. Patient received breathing treatments, Solu-Medrol and gentle hydration.  She was subsequently admitted to inpatient.   Social history:  Patient admits to drinking approximately 0.5 gallons of vodka per week.  She denies ever having issues withdrawing from alcohol.  Patient smokes half pack per day since the age of 12.  Other past medical history reviewed and updated in the chart.  8/30/21: Brief hospital course: Patient is a pleasant 55 yo F who presented on 8/25/21 with SOB x 3-4 days. SYMPTOM_TEXT: This was my booster shot and it?s important to note I had the same reaction in my 2 dose series on 04/21/21.  My symptoms included full body muscular spasms. It felt like I was being electrocuted. It felt like I had Charlie horses, shin splints, and severe growing pains in my legs to start and then progresses throughout my body. Muscles I have never felt before were spasming and throbbing including my inner ear canal.   On the night that I got the vaccine I broke out in full body tremors for an hour from 12:00am to 1:00am (12/4/21 technically). I?ve never had tremors or anything like that before.   My arms had such intense pain and I my fingers were getting stuck and unable to bend. The only thing that made me feel better was intense compression I tried to squeeze my arms as hard as I could.   At one point on the afternoon of 12/4/21 I got up from bed and had an intense stabbing spasm pain in my mid back and it shot down my legs and it caused me to buckle my knees and fall into a wall.   I was deeply uncomfortable in my own skin - I wasn?t able to get comfortable by any means. I was able to take a prescribed muscle relaxer to help me get to sleep.   Then on the night of 12/4 into 12/5 I sweated through my pajamas and woke up at 3am and had to change. It was like I showered. That lasted until I re awoke at 9:30am.  Now on 12/5/21 I feel fine with some residual soreness from the constant spasming and feelings of being electrocuted. My body just feels beat up.
PRIOR_VAX: Moderna, 2nd dose on April 21 2021 - Covid 19 vaccine, 28 years of age.

The following are notes of doctors from his er admission the day after the injection and the day of the patient's death.  74-year-old male with multiple health problems presents to the ED via ambulance with chief complaint generalized weakness, difficulty ambulating and history of fall x2 within the past 24 hours.  Patient had Covid 19 booster shot on Friday and his current symptoms started Saturday morning. Typically uses W/C and walker for ambulation.   Patient denies fever or chills.  No chest discomfort.  Patient states baseline shortness of breath.  No new cough.  No new onset abdominal pain and no urinary symptoms.  Patient does complain of mild pain to the right hip and right knee resulting from his previous fall.  No head injury.  No loss of consciousness.  Current GCS is 15.  Past medical history includes: Chronic atrial fibrillation on Eliquis, CAD/CABG/cardiac stents, CHF, CKD(baseline GFR 20), GERD, COPD, OSAP--nighttime O2, prior DVT/IVC filter, diabetes, obesity, prior admit for symptomatic anemia requiring blood transfusion  Code summary.  I was called to the bedside at 2023 for cardiac arrest.  Nurse states that patient was admitted yesterday for generalized weakness and falls and had been doing well but became unresponsive while she was talking to them.  He began having agonal respirations.  He was noted to be pulseless and CPR was started.  Upon my arrival CPR was in progress and patient was being bagged.  He was having agonal respirations and initially was noted to be in sinus rhythm.  He subsequently went into ventricular fibrillation and was shocked multiple times.  He was given multiple medications including amiodarone, calcium, epinephrine and bicarbonate.  Patient was intubated using video laryngoscope and 8 oh ET tube.  Patient had bilateral breath sounds and positive capnography.  Despite multiple rounds of medications and defibrillation's patient had no return of spontaneous circulation.  Another defibrillator was even brought into the room for dual sequential defibrillation with no change in rhythm.  Time of death was noted to be 2047.  I called the son and advised him of his father's passing. Wife states patient began feeling unwell the day after the injection and rapidly declined. She is concerned his death is a result of it.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Sharp sciatic nerve pain along right lower extremity beginning at buttocks region and radiating down right thigh. Exacerbated by lying down (supine and prone), standing upright (when weight was on the right leg), and sitting crossed leg. At times the pain was pulsating in the thigh area, but remained constant in buttocks. Sitting upright with legs hanging off the bed alleviated some of the pain. Lasted from 11:00PM until time of falling asleep (2:47AM). Stretching, cold compress, naproxen 500mg temporarily eased the pain, but did not stop it. Woke up the next morning (~10:00AM) with no pain, and it has not been back since the time of writing this.
CUR_ILL: Upper respiratory infection (COVID negative) at the beginning of November 2021 (no fever, no sore throat, no difficulty breathing).
HISTORY: Poly cystic ovarian syndrome  Chronic migraines

I have never, ever had allergies, hives or any rashes in my entire life. I can barely sleep. The hives started on my thighs then my upper arms and hands and now are on my ankles and lower legs. It is absolutely horrendous and I have a very hard time sleeping. As soon as some blisters seem to heal and go away, i develop new ones. The pharmacists suggested I take Claritin and Benadryl and use cortison cream. I have read on blogs many many other people are experiences similar hives after their covid vaccines. I am terrified this might be permanent. I really hope not. I have nevver ever had hives or allergies to anything and have no underlying health problems. I am a fit female 49 years old.

Approximately 5 days after receiving this booster dose of the COVID-19 vaccine, I began experiencing extremely heavy menstrual bleeding and clotting.  The bleeding and clotting began on November 3, 2021.  It is currently December 6, 2021 and I am still experiencing heavy bleeding with clotting, and now some cramping as well.   A few days after receiving my first dose of the Moderna vaccine on January 7, 2021, I experienced the same heavy bleeding and clotting. I made an urgent appointment with my OB/GYN on January 14, 2021 and was started on hormone therapy (Megace) to control the bleeding. At the time, I did not connect the bleeding with the vaccine. Following my second dose of the Moderna vaccine on February 4, 2021, the bleeding and clotting began again.  After multiple attempts, I was unable to wean from the Megace without experiencing heavy bleeding.  I underwent an endometrial ablation on August 12, 2021.  Samples of uterine tissue were sent to pathology at that time, and cancer was not detected and was ruled out as a reason for the bleeding. Following the ablation, I had minimal bleeding during menstruation.  On October 29, 2021, I received the booster dose of the Moderna vaccine, and by November 3, 2021 I was again experiencing severe bleeding and clotting, with some days being worse than others.  I was supposed to have an appointment on February 11, 2022, as a follow-up for my endometrial ablation.  I have had to move that appointment up to December 10, 2021, as my provider and I will have to discuss what to do now.  Hormone therapy is not a long-term solution, so it's possible that I will have to undergo a hysterectomy. I will know more after my appointment on December 10, 2021.

RN had Parent place child on the floor and put his feet up on the chair. The RN started talking to the patient and sent another staff member to get another RN, ice packs, juice/gummies, and the BP cuff. Client was lethargic but conscious while the nurse was present. Parent stated that he did pass out. He wasn?t worried because this was common in their family (Dad and sister both commonly had moments like this with shots). RN continued to monitor and assess for signs of syncope. Parents declined any Rescue measures. Client stated an extra 20 minutes after the episode and left without further incident.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: After receiving the booster (7 months after the second vaccine), I began having chills, high fever, muscle aches, stiff neck, sore arm and headache. BUT!! The heart symptoms were different than SVTs. I was having extreme pounding, especially at bed time. The heavy, erratic pounding would be so bad that I would  get an instant headache. Additionally, 4 days after receiving the booster, I tested positive for Covid - with Covid symptoms!!!! Therefore, when I contacted my physician with the concerning cardiac symptoms, they couldn't administer an EKG until my quarantine was over. By the time the quarantine was over the cardiac symptoms had subsided. I am convinced they were a result of the booster.

33yo female patient present for 2nd dose Pfizer Vaccine (Lot FJ8762) on 12/5/21 at 17:48. Immediately after injection felt tingling in arms and short of breath. A cup of water was given to the pt and was instructed to perform deep breathing exercises. Pt continued to look labored breathing. Clinical lead was brought in with an EMS kit. Vital signs were taken. Initial BP 124/84, O2 98%, HR 68. At 1750pm, pt's seen to have swelling of lips and diffuse rash. Received 1 dose of 0.3mg of epinephrine lot #G210304x exp 08/2022. 911 was called at 1751pm. Pt was moved from chair to the floor. At 1758, repeat BP 128/70, O2 SAT 89%, HR 198 per pulse oximeter. Palpated pulse slower correlated with 100 bpm.   At 1800pm, temperature 98, HR 215 per pulse oximeter. Pulse on palpation correlated with 150. AED placed for rhythm analysis.   1802pm, Fire department arrived. Was instructed to remove pads and supplemental O2 was applied to pt. Pt reported feeling now numbness to face, site arm, and bilateral lower extremities. Also complained of generalized heaviness to body.   At 1808pm, EMS arrived. Vital signs taken, BP 124/82, HR 95%. EMS assessment of pt conducted. Last set of vitals BP 135/82, HR 95.   At 1813, pt was placed on a stretcher and brought to the ambulance for further evaluation and disposition. Left for the emergency room.

11 days after receiving the booster shot, I woke up with extreme itchiness on my head and behind ears. They were very red. Later throughout the day, it spread to my entire body and I was covered in huge hives that became worse upon scratching or touching my skin. It was unbearable and benadryl did not help. I went to urgent care and they said my throat was clear--I was advised to take benadryl and see an allergist. The hives at this point were on my elbows, stomach, breasts, everywhere. My feet and hands were swollen and physically hurt. I could not walk properly. This continues every single day. I have seen 2 allergists who confirmed I am not allergic to anything and this was not caused by food or any product I used. They both believed this could have been caused by the vaccine and recommended over the counter antihistamines. I have been taking 4x the normal daily dose and still experience extreme itchiness. Nothing gives me relief--every day I take two oatmeal baths, apply topical cortisone, and take the antihistamines. This is very unbearable and difficult to experience. Please, please look into this and do what you can to inform the public and find a solution for those suffering. It has now been almost 2 weeks and I am still experiencing these symptoms.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: About 45 minutes after receiving vaccination, my arm became weak. After that, my face and left side of my tongue became numb. We had to call 911. EMT came and assessed me. I felt pins and needles in my arm. They gave and administered Benadryl for me. I was taken to the ER. I had dysarthria, slow speech where I could speak but couldn't form full sentences. I noticed a temperature difference between my left & right sides of my body. I woke up at 2am and felt shot in my right deltoid and couldn't move my arm. I had MRI, MRA, CAT scans conducted in the ER. Thursday morning I was discharged and the pain reoccurred Thursday evening and the shooting arm pain happened again Friday. I noticed the temperature difference of both sides of my body. I couldn't recollect/remember things that occurred that day and kept losing time while trying to complete my daily routine. I didn't feel like myself and had high impulsivity. I had sharp shooting headaches and nausea episodes that developed. I saw my PCP and asked for a referral to a neurologist and allergist. That Saturday, I had a high sense of urgency. I had new axleria and my left arm felt weak, I was given 2 ibuprofen to help reduce the pain. The physical symptoms had me weak and I couldn't do anything. I had bad arm pain on Monday and called/connected with Moderna, got a case # with rep. I saw Dr., a neurologist who conducted neuropathic tests on me and informed me to  stay out of work until the 22nd. By Wednesday,  both arms calmed down, not so much pain. lighter sensation. I had an EEG done at Hospital. On Thursday, I could walk outside, could do more normal routine and steadily increased daily routine into the weekend with breaks in between; I had some left side chest pain that woke me up at night but reduced by morning.
ALLERGIES: Tetracycline Latex Demerol Codeine Clindamycin Amoxicillin

That evening at about 5-6pm I started feeling achy and feverish, I did not take my temperature though. I did not feel good all around. I took some ibuprofen 2x. About 10-11p I took 2 more ibuprofen and then went to bed. I honestly have no idea what happened, but I woke on the floor 1am-2am. I had fallen out of bed and was in pain, I was sweating all over, I was feverish, I felt nauseous and felt like I was going to pass out. It woke my husband up because it was so loud. I'm not sure if I had hit the side table drawer that was open with my shoulder or hit the floor hard when I fell. I tried to go back to bed but couldn't sleep because it hurt so bad. The next morning 1/24/2021 it was excruciating so we looked for an ER that didn't have a really long wait time we went around at 8am. We went to a local health care facility. They did an X-ray and said it was broken and needed to put a brace system on it. They gave me a pain medication but I can't recall what. Then they referred me to a orthopedic surgeon. I told them I had just gotten the vaccine but they did not say anything. I was there for about 8-9 hours. On Weds 1/27/2021 I saw an Orthopedic Surgeon at the office I already went to for my back, not the one I was referred to because they could get me in a lot sooner. He took my cast off to do several more x-rays and showed me the severity of the break and the ball of the shoulder was in several pieces. He did not recommend pinning it back together, he recommended a partial shoulder replacement because there could be other issues from it. He gave me a sling for my shoulder. He had me scheduled the surgery with the surgery scheduler and we scheduled it sometime the first week of February. I had to wear a confining sling for 8-10 weeks than a different one for 6-8 weeks. I started physical therapy in April and still attend. I couldn't work until after 1 week post-surgery. Several post-op follow-ups.
LAB_DATA: X-rays 7-8 times, 2 original shoulder was broken, covid test negative, blood work normal, participant had surgery
OTHER_MEDS: Metoprolol 200mg 2x daily, Flecainide 50mg 2x daily, Diltiazem 240mg daily, Lisinopril 40mg 2x daily, Hydrochlorothiazide 12.5mcg daily, Gabapentin 300mg, Ibuprofen 200mg 2x that evening 1/23/2021

SYMPTOM_TEXT: This is a 94-year-old female brought in by EMS given family's concern for decreased oral intake over the past several days and apparent lower chest/upper abdominal discomfort, in the setting of progressive dementia with behavioral disturbances, IDDMII (HbA1c 6.6% 5/2017), Hypothyroidism, Osteoporosis and remote history of CABG, found to be afebrile and hemodynamically stable, agitated, disoriented, clinically dehydrated and uncomfortable appearing on exam, labs notable for CBC and electrolytes within normal limits, sOsm elevated 299, BUN 25 and creat 0.9 (baseline ~0.5), Tbili 2.4 and lactate 2.4, COVID positive, CXR with bibasilar infiltrates, admitted to medicine for dehydration and failure to thrive.  Failure to thrive Dehydration Anorexia Hypoalbuminemia / Protein-Calorie malnutrition Clinically dehydrated on exam, with elevated serum osm, BUN/Creat, and borderline AKI, with reported anorexia over the past several days.  Unclear whether this is being driven by acute abdominal symptoms or systemic illness versus progression of underlying dementia and/or inadequate home care. Excepting evident epigastric discomfort, no localizing symptoms on exam/initial studies including abdominal tenderness, evidence of UTI on UA, or bacterial PNA on CXR, however positive for COVID, which raises possibility of systemic inflammation driving these constitutional symptoms. -No significant electrolyte derangements  > Trend elecrtolytes including Phos/Mg -Received IVF in the ED  > Follow up AM lactate  > ongoing maintenance IVF, NS at 100ml/hr -Add CRP, LDH, fibrinogen *Appreciate CM, PT, and Nutrition involvement  Epigastric discomfort noted by family to be clutching her lower chest/upper abdomen. This together with recent anorexia most concerning for intra-abdominal process including gastritis, gastroenteritis, less likely pancreatitis or ACS. Absence of abdominal tenderness, fever, hemodynamic changes, and leukocytosis point away from acute biliary pathology, appendicitis, perforated viscus. -Add lipase -EKG -Trend Bilirubin -Trial famotidine BID  Borderline AKI BUN elevated and Creat elevated from baseline. Most consistent with prerenal AKI. UA without evidence of UTI, reported casts. No recent nephrotoxins. No history to suggest obstruction. s/p IVF -Trent BUN/Creat -Strict I/Os, monitor volume status:  Goal for euvolemia > Bladder scan if UOP down > Further workup with Urine micro and Urine lytes if worsening  COVID-19 disease Acute hypoxic respiratory failure COVID-19 disease, due to SARS-CoV-2 infection +SARS-Cov-2 PCR 11/25 Symptom onset: several days prior to admission, anorexia, epigastric pain (?) Identifiable exposures: None Initial labs notable for: Normal CBC, CMP with Tbili 2.4, elevated CRP, fibrinogen, LDH Initial chest imaging with bibasilar opacities. On presentation, neither hypoxic nor tachypneic (however pulse ox on ear). On arrival in the RCU, sats 80s on room air, up to mid 90s on 5L. Low clinical suspicion for PE in the absence of symptoms or signs of DVT on exam, pleuritic chest pain, hemoptysis, likewise absence of chest pain, anginal equivalents or acute ischemic changes points away from ACS.   Deferring further workup with D-dimer and troponin at this point. -Admit to RCU: contact/airborne precautions -Supplementary Oxygen: Titrate O2 92-96% -Dexamethasone 6mg daily x 10 days or until discharge -Remdesivir 200mg x 1, 100mg every 24h x 4 doses > monitor renal function and liver chemistries -Strict I/Os, monitor volume status:  Goal for euvolemia -Encourage incentive spirometer use and proning -APAP PRN for pain/fever -Albuterol PRN for wheezing -Benzonatate PRN for cough > Discharge planning Ambulatory O2 challenge daily (once O2 req stable < 4L)
HISTORY: hypothyroidism, osteoporosis, hx of CABG, dementia, type 2 diabetes, onychomycosis
ALLERGIES: codeine - unknown, ibuprofen- unknown, propoxyphene- unknown, ace inhibitors- unknown

She did state that they have a at home nebulizer if needed, she was advised that if in the case the child needed a breathing treatment to provide it and transport to local emergency department. SYMPTOM_TEXT: I received my COVID vaccine and then following that I received my flu shot. Right after receiving the COVID vaccine I had a headache for a couple days and pain for about a week. I also had heavy fatigue. I was hospitalized 1 week later due to breathing issues. I had low oxygen saturation down to the high 60s and low 70s range. It was unclear to my neurologist and pulmonologist whether if the combination of those two vaccines worsened my Myasthenia gravis. The treatment I was on for Solaris may not of have been no longer treating me effectively. I had did well during the summer but I had an underline protection from IVIg. I have been having that IVIg infused every 3 weeks for 80grams. I was receiving those from June-August 2021. My doctors are not sure if the vaccine and flu vaccine contributed to my event. They said it was possible that the IVIg had just ran out. I had a n event in November as well and went to the hospital. I had a plasma exchange. They did that for 3 days in a row. They gave me a liter of fresh frozen plasma the last two days. That treatment worked well on me. In the last past week I have started to have lower oxygen levels again. My doctors are concerned that the vaccination caused my Myasthenia gravis to decline.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Case was hospitalized for and died of Covid 6 months after completing Covid vaccine series.  Patient is an 84 year old male, vaccinated against COVID-19, with a history of valvular and ischemic heart disease who was initially diagnosed with COVID-19 pneumonia on September 30. He presented to the hospital on October 13 with worsening shortness of breath. Initial workup was consistent with coronary ischemia and acute heart failure in addition to COVID-19 infection. He was admitted to the hospital and treated for heart failure, acute coronary syndrome, and COVID-19. Over the course of the first night of his hospitalization the patient developed rapidly worsening gas exchange and was transferred to the ICU. Point of care echocardiography revealed markedly abnormal LV systolic function consistent with an acute MI and systolic heart failure. Given the constellation of acute physiologic insults and his baseline poor health, goals of care discussions were conducted with the patient and his family regarding his very grim prognosis for survival from his critical illness. The patient was made DNR. On the morning of October 14 the patient developed worsening shock physiology, ultimately resulting in cardiac arrest. The patient expired at 09:45 on October 14 with family at the bedside.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Itchy skin. When scratch skin turns red and bumps appear, itches more. Benadryl helps relieve itchiness. Redness goes away within a few hours if not scratched. Cortizone 10 helps relieve itchiness. Itchiness is all over body, though not all at once. Random spots will be itchy, then a different spot later. Itchiness started about 10 days after booster. Visited doctor the next day. Also started a new probiotic around that time. Immediately stopped taking that. Suggested claritin daily, benadryl as needed, and once a day singulair for a week. Symptoms somewhat improved but did not go away. Benadryl was most helpful. A week later (10 days after first symptoms), stopped singulair and started with prednisone. Probiotic was unlikely bc ongoing reaction. Stopped all other vitamins, still taking sertraline. 6 day course starting with 30mg decreasing 5mg each day. Prednisone didn't really seem to help. Itchiness was worst just before bed. Had to take benadryl + pain killer (tylenol while on prednisone, otherwise ibuprofen) to get to sleep. Able to sleep through the night with that. Prednisone course is done now and still itchy. Have another dr appointment tomorrow (~2.5 weeks after symptoms started, 4 weeks after booster shot).
OTHER_MEDS: Sertraline, culturelle women's probiotic, women's multivitamin, emergenc+
