Case was hospitalized for Covid after completing the Covid vaccine series.  He presented with sepsis physiology including fevers and tachycardia as well as shortness of breath and cough. Initiated on broad-spectrum antibiotics given risk for complex catheter related urinary tract infection and pneumonia. Covid test was positive. Chest x-ray did not show significant infiltrate initially.   Started aggressive treatment for Covid with remdesivir and then steroids started shortly thereafter because hypoxia rapidly developed and he required significant respiratory support. CT chest 10/12 showed no PE. Some perihilar infiltrate and bibasilar infiltrate noted as well. CT abdomen/pelvis did not show any acute problems. Baricitinib started on 10/13 as well because of significant hypoxia likely related to Covid. By 10/14 oxygen requirements had markedly improved. For several days prior to discharge, he was on room air during the day and 8 L of oxygen overnight, which is his home dose. Sputum production was not increased over baseline for several days prior to discharge.

I was in a very intense training phase for a martial arts promotion and it was very hot weather. After a practice session and the AC was unable to keep up, I started feeling kind of weak and had mild chills. I rested for a couple days, and went again and had a similar feeling. First was Monday, second was Wednesday. Some time Thursday, I checked my temperature and I had a fever. I had dark urine and I was weak. I took off Thursday from work, and I couldn't work properly on Friday. My training the next week, I could not train properly. I took a quick COVID test Friday 7/23 and COVID PCR test 7/24 and they were both negative. I went to go see my doctor 7/26 and she prescribed lab work and we talked about them a few days later. She concluded diverticulitis. I had no appetite, I had to go to the bathroom a lot. Diarrhea. The most important thing was that I had abdominal discomfort. Timeline: 7/19 started, 7/21 ? knew I didn't feel right. 7/22 sinus pain and fever. Headaches. 7/26 ? started to feel better, but weakness and intestinal discomfort. Dark urine cleared by then. Rhabdomyolysis possibly & diverticulitis. Gave me antibiotics and took it easy.  Weakness lasted for 6 weeks, and gradually became better within those weeks. Weakness is still there but hard to measure. Didn't think that it may have anything to do with the vaccine, but unsure. Urgent care visit - due to COVID tests.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: A few days prior to 03/02/2021, I was feeling like I was in a trance. I could not think, I could not concentrate, I  could not remember. On 03/02/2021- I went into see my cardiologist for an annual check up.  I was not able to walk very far. It felt like I was going to collapse. The cardiologist put me on oxygen. They checked my oxygen level and my oxygen was below 85. On Saturday, I got real numb in my arm and legs and I called my husband and he took me to the hospital. We thought I was having a stroke. On Saturday,  03/06/2021- at about 2:00PM ET,  My husband took me to the  Hospital Emergency Room and they admitted me to the hospital. The hospital thought I was having a stroke, but that was  not the problem. They never did find out what the problem was. Doctor   saw me in the hospital, my pulmonary doctor had all kinds of tests done,  and exhausted all the test he needed to be done on me, but did not know what happened to me. They discharged me from the hospital on Tuesday afternoon. Treatment: oxygen, they had to increase from 2 to 4. It took about 5 or 6 months for me to stop having the memory, concentration,  and forgetfulness.  Those symptoms slowly came back, but my breathing did not get any better with the oxygen.

She said she felt a little tired and wanted to rest. I returned home at around 10:45am. I found her laying in the bed and she was cold to the touch. I performed CPR until the ambulance arrived about 15 minutes later. The EMTS tried to revivie her and then rushed her to the ER. When I arrived the Dr. said that they were unable to revive her by any means they had tried. The doctor informed me that patients heart had just stopped beating. I'm am completely convinced that the second Pfizer vaccine had a diverse effect on patient and contributed to her heart ceasing to function.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Fever, swollen at injection site, itching.

On 3/15/2021, visited Doctor due to swollen leg and rash.  Initially thought it was due to a injury. However, upon further exam, determined that could be due to possible adverse effect to Covid-19 vaccine.   At this point, rash was isolated to lower leg calves.  Rash was raised, deep red, and draining.  Prescribed Doxycycline Monohydrate 100 mg Oral Tab and Betamethasone Valerate 0.1 .  Symptoms did not improve;  On 3/21/2021, visitied Urgent Care, due to worsening symptoms.  Rash was spreading, and still draining.  Told to stop Doxycycline. On 9/29/2021, was prescribed Prednisone On 9/8/2021.  However, upon finishing round of Prednisone, symptoms came back.   On 9/8/2021, visited another doctor with continuing symptoms. Last Derm Diagnosis was severe asteatotic exzema with statis dermatitis.  Culture showed group B staph infection. At this point was referred to Dermatology .  In the meantime, continue with steroid cream, added HCTZ.   On 10/26/2021, was seen by a doctor at Dermatology.  The rash has now spread throughout the body with continued drainage.  Papules, plaques, and patches were found .  Associated diganoses was Pruritus and hypersensitivity reaction to the vaccine.  Was prescribed loratadine,  10 mg., hydroxyzine 25 mg, . Biopsy taken of skin was inconclusive.  On 11/23/2021 was seen again by Dr. at dermatology.  No improvement on symptoms.  Two biopsies were now taken. { Currently awaiting results}.  Was prescribed Bactrim 800 Mg , Hydroxyzine 50 mg., Mupirocin.  To date, symptoms are still present, and no improvement.  Symptoms had started to  subside in a small matter approximately Aug/Sep, (2nd dose of Pfizer vaccine was received 2/19/2021,  however upon receiving  Booster vaccine in October, symptoms increasingly returned with no relief, and no matter what treatment has been provided, no subsiding of symptoms..  Itching is intense, and now, new symptom is leg numbness.  Increasingly alarmed that infection is not under control and could lead to serious further complications. Today, SEVERE drainage is being experienced on hand , and cannot be seen by my Dr until tomorro 12/7/2021.

Case died of Covid after completing the Covid vaccine series.  Patient is a 75 y.o. female with a history of OSA, afib, COPD, who presented to the ED after being found down at home. Was last seen by friends on Saturday (3 days ago). Was found down by neighbors Tuesday (10/5). She had some altered mental status on presentation and tested positive for covid in the ED. CXR with findings suspicious for COVID pneumonia. She does have a history of a pleural effusion, but based on imaging, it looked like COVID was by far the driver for her respiratory failure. Patient's closest relative is her sister-in-law. ICU physician called sister-in-law and it was determined that patient would not want intubation or CPR. The admitting physician spoke with sister-in-law as well. She relayed that patient had been in general poor health and declining recently and had made comments indicating that she may die soon. The poor prognosis for covid patients who are intubated was discussed with sister-in-law. Sister-in-law confirmed that patient's wishes are consistent with DNR/DNI. Due to respiratory failure and hypotension, she was given a fluid bolus and high flow nasal cannula in the ED. Patient did not show any improvement. Admitting physician asked patient very clearly if she would want us to continue or treat her for comfort. She opened her eyes and yelled "comfort!" which was difficult to interpret given her encephalopathy. However, Patient confirmed that she would like only comfort measures did not want to be admitted to the ICU. She also confirmed that Patient would not want renal replacement therapy given her degree of renal failure presently. Patient was admitted to the medical floor where she remained hypoxic and tachypneic. She was supported on comfort care status and was treated with medications to alleviate her symptoms. Patient was accompanied by two of her friends at the bedside. Patient passed away peacefully at 0047 10/6/2021. Family was updated by nursing.

Hospitalized 11/24/2021; COVID-19 positive 11/24/2021; fully vaccinated  BRIEF OVERVIEW:  Admission Date: 11/24/2021 Discharge Date: 11/26/2021 DETAILS OF HOSPITAL STAY: PRESENTING PROBLEM: Weakness [R53.1] Hypoxia, sleep related [G47.34] Fall, initial encounter [W19.XXXA] COVID-19 [U07.1]   HOSPITAL COURSE: Patient is an 85 year old female with a history of OSA, Meniere's disease, chronic kidney disease, and deafness in the right ear who presented to the ER on 11/24 with weakness and fall after 4 days of sinus congestion and cough.   The patient has an abrasion posterior lateral to her left eye as a result of the fall.  The patient had an oxygen desaturation to 87% in ER and was stable on 2 liters supplemental oxygen per NC. Other vital signs were stable except for an occasional high blood pressure read. Lab work showed kidney function at patient's baseline, indeterminate but stable troponins, and a positive covid test. The patient has received 2 doses of Pfizer Covid vaccine. CT head showed no acute intracranial abnormality. Chest x-ray showed patchy opacities in the left base. The patient was weaned to room air prior to getting to her inpatient room. She was admitted for weakness and falls likely related to Covid infection for further work up and monitoring.   The patient continued on room air while in the hospital.  A home oxygen evaluation showed she maintained 92% saturation with activity on room air; she does not need supplemental oxygen. She was offered MAB therapy but declined at this time.  She did receive two doses of Remdesivir and decadron while inpatient.  She was evaluated by PT and OT. PT recommended home with home health care.  The patient currently has the assistive devices she needs in the home.  She was discharged in stable condition with HHC and recommended follow up with PCP. She was also encouraged to get some sort of alert device incase she falls or is in need of help at home but can't get to the phone. She agreed and will do the research to find the communication aid that fits her needs

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I started a period two months after the 2nd vaccination. I started bleeding very heavily and passing clots. And never stopped until the 1st week in September. It was continuous. I was having severe panic attacks. I could not function throughout the day and they thought I was perhaps menopausal. They did hormone studies and that indicated that I was not close to being menopausal. They also did ultrasounds and found ovarian cysts that were not anything to be concerned about. They also did an endometrial biopsy which was negative. STD panel which was also negative. They had to increase my blood pressure medication to 30mg because my BP was up as well. They started me on Prempro medication because bleeding never stopped, and it was that heavy. She also gave me a prescription for Alprazolam which helped me calm down significantly. After the first month and a half, sometime mid to late August, I started to feel a little better and was able to function throughout the day. The first week in September was the first time I stopped bleeding. After that, my daughter tested positive for COVID in October, and it was two weeks after she initially gotten sick where I started bleeding extremely heavy with lots of clots and that lasted for over 30 days. I did notice the anxiety and the panic attacks, but I was able to manage that. The bleeding just never stopped. During those 3 initial months where I was bleeding as well, I was unable to eat and had no appetite. I could not eat anything so I only drank ice water and was constantly nauseated. I lost 20 lbs in one month. No I'm not bleeding or having symptoms anymore, unsure if this will happen again in the future ER visit was because of headache & panic attack.

Client arrived at clinic for second dose of Pfizer pediatric covid vaccine.  Was happy and healthy appearing before vaccination.  RN asked about response to the first dose and was told she had no difficulty. She was vaccinated at approximate 1600 and instructed to go to observation area with father and brother.  Approximately 10 minutes later, RN was informed that client was in some pain. RNs immediately began to assess.  Client was complaining of pain with inspiration of breath, pointing to center of her chest. Visual inspection showed no rash or hives.  Pulse was 80 bpm and regular. Client did not appear to be in any distress, except that she looked a little sad. We continued to observe for approximately 30 and discussed possible reactions with client's father. At 1630 client and family left the clinic RNs recommendations.  Recommend the client receive children's acetaminophen and continue monitoring by parents.  Call PCP with concerns or go to ER, if condition does not resolve or gets worse. Provided parent with dosing chart by weight for acetaminophen.
LAB_DATA: This RN contacted the family approximately 0800 the next morning to inquire about the client.  Family responded that she was feeling good.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient received only the powder vial of this two part vaccine.  It was inadvertently diluted with sterile water diluent instead of the included part two liquid vial.  This dose was deemed invalid and was repeated on 11/29/2021  The root cause of this error is due to the packaging by manufacturer.  Unlike all other vaccines, this two part vaccine must be mixed together in order to be effective.  It is not a sterile water diluent like our other vaccines.   Other vaccines packaged this way come as 10 vials in a box = 10 doses.  Menveo is 5 vials each of the liquid and powder therefore only 5 doses.  The two vials do not come "attached" in any way.  GSK knows this is an issue and therefore has created bands that we can pair the vials to each other after opening.  In a busy clinic, or new staff when the box is opened its easy for staff to pull just one vial - if its the powdered vial - reconstituting with sterile water diluent like other powedered vaccines is a common error.  If the liquid vial is pulled, its easy to administer just this liquid without mixing.    When this happens, its difficult to trace to one patient therefore often the entire 5 doses need to be tracked and revaccinated since its difficult to know who may have received the correct dose vs incorrect.   In this instance an inexperienced MA administered the powder only, diluted with water to a total of 4 patients before the error was discovered.      Recommended packaging change so that it is very clear that its a two part vaccine , perhaps a peel pack with the two vials together or apply the band before packaging instead of having the end user apply the band.  Better yet. similar to solumedrol vials - its one vial with two chambers, that when the lid is pushed down, it pushes the rubber stopper and the two parts mix together.  This would also prevent unnecessary access to the vial with needles to remove and inject into the other.
OTHER_MEDS: betamethasone dipropionate (DIPROSONE) 0.05 % ointment  desonide ointment 0.05 % ointment

Patient woke up on Thursday (Dec 2) complaining of widespread muscle/joint pain.  no headache, neck pain only when moving head, walking like 80 yo man. Significant limp was present, and he was almost unable to walk up/down stairs. Right leg is worse, hurts to bend knee. little to no energy and not wanting to move around. Unable to bend to pick things up off the floor.  Drinking significantly less than normal. Took him to urgent care - they tested for covid (negative) and said to follow up with doctor after a few weeks. We talked to the nurse at the pediatricians office that same day - they made an appointment for that afternoon. We saw the doctor he did a number of tests (I'll include those in the next line), did an assessment and said it was likely post-viral myositis. (negative for strep, both flu's, and negative urine sample) Sent us home to push liquids and rest.  Patient slept poorly, waking frequently (which is not normal for him.) When he woke up Friday morning (Dec 3) around 6:30 am he was unable to keep liquids down. He puked 3-4 times over a 2-3 hour period before being able to slowly rehydrate. His energy was really low, and he had a dusty looking rash over/around his left eye (with mild swelling).  Symptoms started diminishing Saturday morning (Dec 4), and had reduced to only mild limping by the time of our follow up that afternoon. Lab results were all normal.  Symptoms almost entirely gone today (Dec 6) at our 2nd follow up.
LAB_DATA: All lab results were negative/within normal ranges. All done on Dec 2nd.  Covid-19 CK COMPREHENSIVE METABOLIC PANEL C-REACTIVE PROTEIN SEDIMENTATION RATE ALDOLASE URINALYSIS  INFLUENZA A/B  STREP A

January 21, 2021: Moderna dose 1 LT arm. Band-Aid had a tiny blood. Very sore arm for 4 days. Felt alert. Had a pimple at injection site for a week and mild bump for months. Couple days later my right foot (history of injury in about 2000) started to get super painful, discolored, inflamed, bulge and tingly.  February 11, 2021: Provider appointment. Prescribed prednisone for 5 days. X-rays at provider and Podiatrist show minor results. Start of a bunion and bone spurs on the bottom and sides of foot. February 18, 2021: Moderna dose 2 LT arm. Band-Aid had no blood. That night felt flushed with a temperature of 96, had chills that night and could not warm up. Sore arm for a few days. Diarrhea. Developed headache at day 5. Stomach tenderness starts at day 6 and gets worse on day 7. Day 10 and Day 11 saw large crystal in my eyes those two days for about an hour each day one weekend and then the following weekend. Closed eyes and was not visible. Right foot continued to hurt and tingle. Left hip (history of injury 2010) starts to hurt really badly. Took Aleve and made it feel better also. Back and lung tenderness. Menses minor changes, heavier and less days. April 26, 2021: Provider appointment. Physical evaluation. Blood results within normal limits. Prednisone for 5 days. Referral to physical therapy and to orthopedics at my request. May 4, 2021: Physical therapy appointment. Evaluated, planned and treated for steroid rub on groin area and taught six exercises done 2 to 3 times a day.  May of 2021: Left ear starts issues (history of injury fall on back of head 2015). Mild highway sound at first then ringing. Possible mild hearing loss. Feeling plugged. June 7, 2021: Provider appointment. Sound of a huge fan/highway in my left ear unable to sleep and setup an appointment. Ear was cleaned wax chunks. Prescribed cetirizine. Would help then it would come back. Took ibuprofen 2 pills 2 times day for 5 days and needed more water intake to not land in ER. Felt it did something at that time. Referral to ENT. July 27, 2021: MRI on left hip. Physiological amount of fluid. Full thickness labral tear. August 3, 2021: Orthopedics appointment. Physical evaluation and was told to go back to physical therapy, continue exercises and use foam roller because hip was not that bad and moving. Physiological amount of fluid on MRI. Diagnosed with tendonitis bursitis. Pain under control with exercises a month later and exercises down to one time a day. October 19, 2021: Chiropractor rehab appointment. Said ?felt C1 bulge? had x-rays. Results days later, Congenital last two cervical spine round pieces fused. Treatment planned for tinnitus and treatment on hold. October 21, 2021: Provider appointment for head and neck. X-rays done and Congenital last 2 cervical spine round pieces fused. Head exercises. Blood work within normal limits. October 22, 2021: Ear Nose and Throat appointment. Examined ruled out lots. No hearing loss. Ordered MRI contrast to ensure no masses near the ear. Told to take lipoflavonoid for 2 months straight. I noticed changes within the first week. There is a big difference before and after taking lipoflavonoid.  November 2, 2021: MRI contrast for ears and head done and results within normal limits received Nov 2, 2021.  Nov 26 2021: Moderna dose 3rd LT arm. I wanted same type and same location to stay where they are. Band-Aid had tiny bit of blood. Arm sore, achy and tingly for a few days. Ran and agitated the RT foot. Stomach tenderness few days out. Mild highway sound and ringing in left ear 10 days later. Got to start running weeks before and felt great to not be in pain. Would like to add to this in years to come for the outcome of the 3 inflamed body parts. Appointment with allergist February 15, 2021.

Silver-dollar sized rash appeared in center of patient's back (along spine) on Weds, 11/24/2021. We assumed she was having an eczema flare. My son and I have occasional flares, and it looked similar. She said it was a bit sore, and itchy (we told her not to scratch or rub it).  I did not call the pediatrician right away, as I noticed it the evening before a holiday weekend. Decided to treat it with Hydrocortisone and Benadryl, which I had on hand and call on Monday if it hadn't gotten better or worsened, so we could see about getting a prescription. Over the weekend, a scattering of small spots popped up along her ribcage, under her left armpit, aligned with the spot on her back, and the spot on her back became more irritated (raised and bumpy). Called the pediatrician on Monday morning, 11/29, and was able to get her in right away. Her usual pediatrician is was not available so we saw another doctor. He checked the spots and immediately identified them as shingles. It had not occurred to me that it could be shingles, as patient received her Varicella vaccine doses on 02/28/2012 and 11/12/2015, and has never exhibited any Chicken Pox symptoms. Doctor said since she was already five days from the spots appearing, and they had not opened/bled, we did not need to treat with a prescription. He recommended we treat with Calamine, Benadryl and Ibuprofen. It is not causing ongoing pain, but will cause a quick burst of pain if the shingles are  accidentally pushed or rubbed against. As of today, the rash has gone down significantly. The spots on her ribcage are very small (they almost look like little chicken pox now) and the spot on her back has reduced by about half.  Patient had an appointment for her second vaccine dose on 12/1. Doctor advised we keep the appointment, as it was seven days after her symptoms appeared. The shingles have not flared up again since she received her second dose.

Normal immunogenic response day of and after vaccine (headache, nausea, fatigue, aches, "felt under water" that went away normal function from time of booster 11/2-11/15- able to do cardio no problem  11/16 felt like I was going to faint during an EMDR therapy session - could be related to trauma processing.  11/17 headache/nausea in am. Was sitting in a meeting and all of a sudden my vision veered. Felt like I was going to faint around 1:30 pm. Then actually Fainted with shaking/fatigue - stayed in bed rest of day 11/19 shortness of breath started -unable to complete my daily half hour walk due to difficulty breathing, very high heart rate that wouldn't come down, dizziness since then have had on and off again headache, high heart rate that persistently stays higher than usual, dizziness especially down stairs, shortness of breath interfering with daily activities, extreme fatigue
LAB_DATA: 11/23 went to PCP based on fainting and symptoms. Blood pressure 118/80 and heart rate 130 sitting down. Based on high heart rate and symptoms she referred me to ER.  11/23 Went to ER.  Two IVs given. Heart rate very high 140s but came down several hours later after two IV fluids. They also did chest x-ray: Findings: Lungs are clear. No pleural effusion or pneumothorax. Cardiac silhouette and mediastinal contours are normal And  several blood tests(CBC with differential,troponin,D-Dimer,B-TYPE NATRIURETIC PEPTIDE, Comp Metabolic Panel,TSH REFLEX FREE T4, CK) and ECG- 12 LEAD WITHOUT RHYTHM.  These were all in range except just barely above range for these: Red Cell Count 5.3 M/uL  Standard: 3.8 - 5.2 M/uL Hemoglobin 15.7 g/dL  Standard: 11.6 - 15.6 g/dL Hematocrit 47 %  Standard: 34 - 46 %  They ruled out things such as myocarditis, blood clots, heart murmur, etc... Said I had mild dehydration. Was referred to a faint and fall clinic for echocardiogram but this hasn't taken place yet . Believe it may be related to my pre-existing POTS. I'm not sure it is related but I did report in my VSAFE check-in and received a call. I was unable to speak to a representative and they said I could report to VAERS online.
HISTORY: POTS, IBS, Lichen planus/sclerosus, essential tremor
ALLERGIES: none that I am aware of

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Some time in the summer, a rash appeared on the back of left hand. Little bumps. Looked like a fungal infection like athletes foot but on your hand. I went a few weeks doing nothing and treated it with antifungal cream. And it itched too. The cream had no effect. After a month or so, I decided to make an appointment with a dermatologist, and it was a 3 week delay before I could see them. About 3 days before my appointment, the rash just completely disappeared and so I  canceled my appointment. And 3 weeks later, it came back and on my other hand and up the wrist, so on both hands. At this point, I went to my family doctor and mentioned what happened with the rash. He prescribed a topical cream that I was to apply 3 times a day. And I applied it and it went away. Then 3 days earlier from today, it came back. Left hand - back of the hand, starts at bone of thirst at base of thumb and wraps around, Right hand - starts at bone of thirst at base of thumb centralized there. The bumps are really tiny, smaller than head of pen. Itchy and can break them open, clear liquid if broke open. The cream didn't do much when I first put the cream on - took about 3 weeks. Fungal cream didn't do anything. Haven't done anything out of the ordinary or changed anything. So this is new.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I received my two initial vaccines from an Hospital mass drive-through event sponsored by my employer. My first shot was in Feb. 2021, the second in March 2021, and the booster in Nov. 2021. All three shots were from Moderna. I felt achy, tired, and unwell after my first shot; all symptoms disappeared within a few days. After the second shot, I ran a fever of 102.5 F, vomited, and had trouble eating or drinking anything without feeling nauseous until the following afternoon. I did not go to work. The fever came down within two days but Tylenol and Advil didn't seem to help much. I received the Moderna half-dose booster through pharmacy on Nov. 12th, 2021, and it was a similar story, only this time the fever went up to 104.1. I ran a temperature of 101 the entire next day (Saturday), 100 the following day (Sunday), and 99 the fourth day after the shot (Monday, Nov. 15th). It took about 4-5 days for my body temperature to return to normal.
LAB_DATA: None. After my second shot, I did call my doctor's office for advice and schedule a virtual visit. He recommended OTC medications and fluids. Otherwise, the symptoms resolved without additional care.
OTHER_MEDS: Paroxetine 40 mg, Wixela 250/50, Azelastine HCL nasal spray 137 mcg, Montelukast 10 mg, Wal-Fex 180 mg, Iron 65 mg, Pantoprazole 40 mg, Diazepam 5 mg (as needed), Albuterol 90 mg (as needed), Dupixent 300 mg/2 ml (once every two weeks)
ALLERGIES: Environmental allergies Nickel allergy Allergic to walnuts and shellfish

Hospitalized (11.30.21);  COVID-19 positive (11.30.21); fully vaccinated  Admission Date: 11/30/2021 Discharge Date: 12/1/21 DETAILS OF HOSPITAL STAY: PRESENTING PROBLEM: Acute appendicitis [K35.80] Acute appendicitis with localized peritonitis, without perforation or abscess, unspecified whether gangrene present [K35.30] HOSPITAL COURSE: Patient is a 51 year old female who presented to the emergency room at hospital on 11/30/21 with concerns of 2 days of periumbilical abdominal pain that eventually moved over to her right lower quadrant. Upon arrival to the a CT scan revealed imaging findings suspicious for acute appendicitis. General surgery was asked to evaluate for a potential appendectomy. After evaluation by the general surgery team, it was decided to take patient to the operating room (OR) for laparoscopic appendectomy for her acute appendicitis after discussing the procedure including risks, benefits & alternatives. In the operating room, the appendix was found to be perforated & was subsequently removed without any complications & she was sent to the post-anesthesia care unit (PACU) in stable condition.  Postoperatively patient was slow to progress and had significant abdominal pain as well as tachycardia and diet intolerance.  On the evening of 12/2 we obtained a CT scan of the abdomen pelvis which showed a few fluid collections concerning for early abscess.  IR was consulted and on 12/05 they were able to aspirate only a few mL of fluid.  After this, the patient reportedly had much improved abdominal pain, was able to tolerate a full meal, was able to ambulate and void independently.  She was discharged home on 12/06 with a course of oral antibiotics and the appropriate follow-up and discharge instructions provided.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: On Sunday, November 21, the patient woke up with mild headache, body aches, and vomiting every time she ate food or drink liquids.  She did have temperatures in the range of 99-100 that day.  On Monday, November 22nd, she had a nosebleed that parents report was uncontrollable and continued for about 30 minutes.  She has not had this previously.  She also developed neck pain on Nov 22 as well, primarily and neck flexion.  She had a temperature to 101 on Monday evening.  The following day, November 23rd, she continued to have an extremely poor appetite with mild headache, she vomited once in the morning after Tylenol and continued to complain of stiff neck.  She continued to have temperatures in the 99 range.  They did take her to urgent care who referred her to ED,  discharged after supportive care. The following day, Wednesday November 24th, she seemed to improve to about 75% of normal.  This continued until Nov 28. On Sunday, November 28th, she awoke with severe neck pain and stiffness as well as a 10/10 headache, the worst of her life.  She vomited x1 prior to eating but may have had a few sips of water at that point. She was subsequently identified as having an arterial venous malformation in the medulla with apparent focus of hemorrhage.
LAB_DATA: MRI Brain w/wo Contrast, November 29, 2021 12:39 CST IMPRESSION:  Arteriovenous malformation in the medulla with apparent focus of hemorrhage.

They could find nothing wrong and prescribed something for stomach cramps and nausea.  I also went to the drugstore and purchased different kinds of indigestion products.  Nothing was really working and I couldn't eat much or sleep. I was reacting in an allergic manner to alot of things.  Finally, I went back to the ER on 11/21/21 and told them I felt I was having many allergic reactions to my food in general and suspected the vaccine booster had put  my immune system in overdrive.  They gave me a steroid shot in the hip and an antihistamine and I felt like I was on the right track. I stepped my immune supplements and ate very carefully, but still wasn't able to eat a regular sized meal until 4 days later.  I am on the  road to recovery, but now am having trouble with hyperthyroidism.  The whole event really messed me up even I was having troubles to begin with, but nothing so extreme.

Approximately 14-16 hours after the second Shingrix shot, I got hot, dizzy, and weak, my throat tightened, and I felt short of breath to the point of almost passing out. At the time I was riding a chair lift at a Ski Area at approximately 12,000 feet. As I unloaded I did not see emergency or ski area personnel. Since I normally do not have asthma symptoms of any kind, my rescue inhaler was in my car. I made my way barely to the car, used the inhaler, and drank a cup of an energy drink in lieu of using an epipen. I did not feel well enough to hike to ski area first aid office, and I waited to see if I should call 911. After about an hour I was somewhat better and drove home carefully. After about a day I felt better. I did not report the event to my physician or pharmacy at that time since I felt better. However, I did mention this event to my doctor's Physician Assistant on October 7 while discussing Covid treatment options, including monoclonal antibody infusion/shot. Preceding this, I had my first Shingrix shot on 10/8/20. Within a few hours I felt dizzy, weak, and terrible, akin to the flu. I had not reported that to my physician or pharmacy since the symptoms cleared a day or two later. Since then, I have been concerned about my body's future reaction to shots of any kind.
HISTORY: Mild asthma without complications; Hyperlipidemia; Mild hypertension; Prediabetes

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Administration Error: 12 children at a recent community vaccination event erroneously received ~25.7mcg of the adult Pfizer formulation instead of the intended 10mcg dose. In this case, the vaccine mixer pulled the Pfizer vaccine for adults/adolescents (purple top; for 12 years +) from the cooler instead of the intended Pfizer Pediatric (orange top; for 5-11 years).  He proceeded to prepare the Adult Pfizer vials following the Pfizer instructions (diluted with 1.3mL diluent and prepared 0.2mL into syringe).  These doses were administered to 12 patients before the error was identified.  All patients did not report any adverse effects during the immediate observation phase, or during phone call follow-up several days following the event.  All patients/parents have been notified of the error, advised that the CDC considers this a valid 1st dose, and will proceed to receive the 2nd dose as scheduled.  Mixing procedures and workflows have been evaluated and adjusted per our safety action plan as a result of this error.

Co lead PHN and LVN received verbal consent from client to re-vaccinate with Moderna COVID-19 booster. Client did not want to switch to left deltoid and wanted vaccine in right deltoid. At 02:58 PM, vaccinating LVN administered Moderna COVID-19 vaccine booster dose lot# 035C21A into right deltoid 1 inch away from previous injection site. Client completed 15 minute observation with no incident. Client was seen leaving vaccination site with steady gait.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: After every COVID vaccination, including booster, about one week later I'd enter a severe depression and have severe anxiety. I have had these feelings before and know well how to handle them and cope. But this was consistent with every dose despite my life circumstances. The intensity was severe, needing me to reach out to my doctors and for help from my family every time. Every time I had to take time off work. After the booster, the depression and anxiety became so severe that I had to check myself into the emergency room to not take my own life. I had a hard time getting help because of the anxiety. And the thoughts in my head were darker then anything I have ever experienced. This occurred 5-7 days after every vaccine. And each time I got another one, the symptoms would persist for longer. If I hadn't had a psychology degree and known to get help for those thoughts, it is very likely that I could have died.

The areas of itchiness migrate to different areas every hour or so, and the skin is blotchy and raised - like a cat has scratched me.  Then for hours at a time, there is no itchiness. I have no food or medication allergies, and I have not changed my lotion, shampoo, detergent, or soap.  I also have not worn any new clothes. SYMPTOM_TEXT: Last year in November I did have COVID. Each time I got the vaccine I would have a headache, a low grade fever, and chills. I would take Tylenol, and it would relieve those symptoms. I started seeing the blood last night. My stools were totally black and loose. I went to bed. Then it did it again and it was getting worse. I went to a hospital. The doctor told me I was bleeding in my sigmoid colon. They placed a temporary clip where the bleeding was coming from. They told me if the bleeding started happening again to go back to the hospital so that they can stop it. I left the hospital on Wednesday. I will see my GI doctor tomorrow. They don't know why it happed and if it will happen again. I do still have loose stool but there is no blood. The whole time I was at hospital I was bleeding. I was prescribed Pepcid, but I have stopped taking it. The doctor also took me off of Spironolactone. I was released from the hospital on 12/3/2021.

LAB_DATA: EKG was normal.  Chest x-ray was negative for acute process.   Blood work did demonstrate a slightly elevated troponin at 55 along with a normal white blood cell count and slightly low hemoglobin at 12.8.  Sodium, potassium and chloride are normal.  BUN and creatinine are normal.  Liver enzymes and total bilirubin are normal.  Glucose was elevated at 192.  The patient is a type II diabetic.  Lactate was normal at 1.8.  TSH was slightly elevated but free T4 was normal.  The initial troponin was 55 and repeat troponin II hours later was 51.  Given that there is no significant change and actually decreasing troponin I do not feel that the elevated troponin is secondary to myocardial infarction.  Given that the patient recently had a Covid vaccine the patient may have a component of myocarditis.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I do not know if the vaccine had any effect on what occurred, but thought it was worth reporting.  I got vaccinated (first dose) a week after my period. I got pregnant that cycle-my first pregnancy. My due date would have been November 13, 2021. At week 5, shortly after I discovered I was pregnant, I began bleeding slightly. At the hospital, after taking an ultrasound they diagnosed me with an angular pregnancy--in other words, the embryo had implanted on the very edge of the uterus. I was advised that this put me at high risk of early miscarriage. I didn't miscarry, and the pregnancy seemed to be going normally for some weeks. At week 15, however, an early anatomy scan revealed severe IUGR-the baby was measuring two weeks behind. Further investigation revealed that the cause was a placenta that seemed never to have formed correctly. By week 25, we were told that the baby was dying, would not survive delivery at that birth weight, and that continuing the pregnancy  was putting me at high risk of complications. Based on this, we chose a medical abortion at 26 weeks. I delivered stillborn; the baby weighed 380 grams, a weight appropriate to 21 weeks.  Doctors do not know exactly what caused the IUGR. But as I tested negative for blood clotting disorders, they said the likeliest culprit is the angular pregnancy. I was also scanned to see if there were any anomalies in my uterine shape to make me more prone to poor embryo implantation, and the test came back normal. Given that I was vaccinated only a week or two before implantation would have occurred, I thought it was at least worth considering if there was a connection.  I was vaccinated in another country. I only received one dose of the vaccine, as I had recovered from  COVID in March 2020 (I had a mild case, with no lingering symptoms). Per the country's vaccination policy, people who have recovered only receive a single dose.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 3 days after the 1st does of the Pfizer vaccine I started to get severe nagging headaches around the crown of my head. After receiving the 2nd dose these headaches have thus continued and are worse. To this day these headaches continue. I delayed to report this adverse event as I hoped they would subside and go away however they are more nagging and bothersome everyday. They are not completely debilitating where I can't function and live life daily however some days they require me to take Excedrin or Motrin to help relieve them to no avail. I historically have never had a history of headaches or migraines. I have otherwise been healthy and there's no added stress or health issues in my life that I can point back to other than this vaccine that correlate to my daily headaches. The headaches start in the morning and progressively get worse as the day goes on in the evening. Some days they are more nagging. The headache hurts around the crown of my head and it's nagging. They don't go away and this makes me very irritable on some days where I can get short tempered with people and also limit my full attention to my work or studies without trying hard to focus. I have not seen a physician about my headaches yet, but I am planning to as they are becoming more of a nuisance. I'd hate to learn that I may have to begin other medical therapies as a result as I am otherwise healthy with no conditions prior.  My arm did hurt after taking the vaccine but nowhere near the level of soreness as the first vaccine. I truly help these headaches go away soon though I am discouraged as it's been 3 months since my second dose. I have heard of several other friends and colleagues with similar issues that received the Pfizer vaccine and some have sought medical treatment to no avail via: primary care physicians, neurologists and pain management specialists.
LAB_DATA: none, other than the vaccine appointment

LAB_DATA: Complete blood workup but nothing unusual was seen. Dr referred me to another Dr for an EMG.  I'm still waiting for a written report.   Note: Dr believes the symptoms may be related to a pinched nerve near L5-S1.  I reminded her that those discs have been in a deteriorated state since May 2006.  Back then, I was in a lot of pain and couldn't walk, sit, stand, or lay down for more than about 5 minutes. I was on Vicodin to manage the pain.  Instead of having surgery, I elected to pursue my own version of PT by combining short walks, stretches, and soaking in warm (almost hot) water.  It took three months (approx), but I was able to recover a full range of motion as my medical history has established.   I have had no impact injuries to any part of my body, nor do I perform any moderate lifting/twisting work (let alone anything that's heavy). So, this sudden onset raises questions in my mind about to the root cause. Also, my wife went throught the same vaccination schedule as I did and has more intense symptoms in the same location.

Patient received booster dose around 6:10 pm. At around 6:25 pm one of my technicians checked on her right after she went back to work and patient reported she saw 3 of the person (visual disturbances due to dizziness). My technician immediately had her sit down, the pharmacist intervened to discuss how she was feeling  (and to confirm no signs of allergic reaction) and what to do if her dizziness got worse, and we provided her water and snacks since she hadn't had anything to eat today besides a Redbull and had vaped before coming to work. Patient stated she was cold so we brought her clothes to help warm up. She sat  for over 30 minutes and stated she was feeling back to normal after eating and drinking and was no longer dizzy or light headed. She indicated she wanted to go to get her lunch and we instructed her to immediately contact an employee if she was feeling light headed, dizzy, cold, or having signs of an allergic reaction. We confirmed with an employee in the front of the store there was nobody that could sit with her in the back room from the front of the store but the patient was adamant she was back to normal and would let someone know if she got lightheaded, dizzy, or cold again. The team lead was aware of the situation and the need to monitor her and let us know immediately of any changes to how she was feeling and when to page the pharmacist. About 15 minutes later I was notified by a team lead that she wasn't feeling well and had vomited bile. A pharmacy technician went back with food and water with strict instructions of when to page the pharmacist to the back and sat with her for over 45 minutes and gave her food and water while getting heaters on her since she was cold. The technician sat with her for over 45 minutes until she was feeling back to normal, color had returned to normal,  she had eaten and drank more food and water, and she was no longer light headed or dizzy.  The pharmacist (reporter) talked with the patient extensively about options to get a ride home (she had no option and declined waiting for a ride from the pharmacist), what to do if she was feeling dizzy, when to call 911, and that she needed to keep someone on the phone with her for entire ride and have them call 911 if she stopped responding to them. We also discussed follow up care when she was home and when to see medical attention.
OTHER_MEDS: ProAir inhaler Inhale 4 puffs by mouth every 4 to 6 hours as needed  Nexplanon inserted November 2019 Nicotine vape -uses about 1 hour total per day of continuous vaping

Patient took aspirin to help, and felt better with fever and body aches after 2 days. Patient reported cold/chill feeling after couple of days.

Exactly 10 days after I received my Moderna booster shoot, I started to experience hives on multiple parts of my body, starting with mostly my hands and neck.  My fingers got swollen to the point where my wedding ring would not come off, so I went to the Emergency Department and they gave me IV solu-medrol, Pepcid, and Benadryl.  The ED doctor also tried to use lubricating jelly to get the ring off, but none of these were able to get it off.  It did prevent my fingers from swelling too much, so I was sent home and prescribed a 4 day treatment of 40mg prednisone daily and 50mg Benadryl every 6 hours.  My ring came off the 3rd night but the hives have persisted, traveling to different parts of my body. They have been on my hands, palms, shins, feet, scalp, back, neck, shoulders, and buttocks. I am still using benadryl nightly and cetirizine during the day, as well as hydrocortisone cream topically when the itching becomes too much.  I have an appointment with the doctor on 12/14 to discuss all of the above.

shingles; Information has been received regarding a case in litigation from a lawyer and referred to a female patient of unknown age. No information was provided regarding medical history, concurrent conditions, or concomitant medications. In or around 2013, the patient was vaccinated with zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX) (dose, route, lot# and expiration date were not reported) for routine health maintenance and for its intended purpose: the prevention of shingles (herpes zoster). Shortly after receiving zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), the patient suffered shingles. As a direct and proximate result of zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), the patient's symptoms had resulted in physical limitations not present prior to using the product. The patient also experienced mental and emotional distress due to resulting physical limitations and seriousness of her condition. As a result of the manufacturer, marketing, advertising, promotion, distribution and/or sale of zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), the patient sustained severe and permanent personal injuries. Further, as a tragic consequence of zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), the patient suffered serious, progressive, permanent, and incurable injuries, as well as significant conscious pain and suffering, mental anguish, emotional distress, loss of enjoyment of life, physical impairment and injury. As a direct and proximate result of zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), the patient had suffered and incurred damages, including medical expenses; the loss of accumulations; and other economic and non-economic damages. The outcome of the event shingles was considered as not recovered. The causality assessment between the event and zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX) was considered as related by the lawyer.    The lawyer considered the event shingles to be disability.

blood clots in lungs; This is a spontaneous report received from a contactable reporter(s) (Consumer or other non HCP) from License Party. The reporter is the patient. Other Case identifier(s): US-BRISTOL-MYERS SQUIBB COMPANY-BMS-2021-125941 (Bristol-Myers Squibb Company).  This spontaneous case was reported by a consumer and describes the occurrence of PULMONARY THROMBOSIS (blood clots in lungs) in female patient of an unknown age who received apixaban (Eliquis) for Cerebrovascular accident prophylaxis. CO-SUSPECT PRODUCTS included Covid-19 Vaccine for COVID-19. On an unknown date, the patient started Eliquis (unknown route) and Covid-19 Vaccine (unknown route). On an unknown date, the patient experienced PULMONARY THROMBOSIS (seriousness criteria hospitalization and medically significant). The patient was treated with Heparin for Pulmonary thrombosis. The action taken with Eliquis(Unknown) was unknown. At the time of the report, PULMONARY THROMBOSIS outcome was unknown. The patient received apixaban for prophylaxis stroke (atrial fibrillation). The patient inquired that if it was safe to take the Covid 19 vaccine with Eliquis. She reported that she had been on Eliquis for at least 2 years or may be 3 because she did not want to deal with the lab work which she later stated was associated with warfarin. She had received both Covid 19 injections and after that within a month she had blood clots in his lungs. The patient stated that she was sick for 4 days in bed and that she could not get enough oxygen. She was taking Eliquis for afib, that she began to get worse all the sudden and her daughter had to call an ambulance for her and was hospitalized for 6 days, placed on a Heparin drip. The patient stated that she never had any problems before with Eliquis that she began this medication because with warfarin there was a time issue and she was frequently having to get stuck. She said that she had to wonder because the blood clots in the lungs came on so suddenly after 2 years of successful use with Eliquis if there was any correlation or association with the use of Eliquis with the Covid 19 vaccine. She mentioned that Eliquis has a 99.9% success rate in doing what is needed for patients, and that she wanted to know why this happened all of the sudden when she had experienced no problems before. For Eliquis(Unknown), the reporter did not provide any causality assessments.  Causality Assessments: Drug = ELIQUIS Event = Thrombosis pulmonary Per Reporter = No Information Per Company (Bristol-Myers Squibb) = Not Related.  Apixaban (ELIQUIS) is under agreement with Bristol-Myers Squibb.  No follow-up attempts are possible; information about lot/batch number cannot be obtained. No further information is expected.; Sender's Comments: This patient had pulmonary thrombosis after receiving apixaban therapy and COVID-19 vaccine. Based on the limited information available regarding event details with relevant medical history and therapy details, it cannot be ascertained with reasonable possibility that apixaban contributed to the reported event.

She said that the physical therapy seems to help with the pain in the shoulder and neck, as well as the tingling in her left hand and fingers. She did not experience it all the time,  the pain came and went. However, the injection site pain was there no matter how much therapy she got and no matter what she was doing. This spontaneous case was reported by a consumer and describes the occurrence of DIPLOPIA (Double Vision), NERVOUS SYSTEM DISORDER (Neurological medical condition), VACCINATION COMPLICATION (adverse reaction to the booster shot), HEAD DISCOMFORT (when she tried to hold her head up, she felt the room going around) and IMPAIRED DRIVING ABILITY (could not drive a car for 5 days) in a 67-year-old female patient who received mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (batch no. 002F21A) for COVID-19 vaccination. The occurrence of additional non-serious events is detailed below. The patient's past medical history included Double vision and Cataract operation (Summer 2021) in 2021. Concurrent medical conditions included Diabetes and Hypothyroidism. Concomitant products included METFORMIN for Diabetes, LEVOTHYROXINE SODIUM (SYNTHROID) for Hypothyroidism, INSULIN GLARGINE (LANTUS) for an unknown indication. On 05-Nov-2021, the patient received third dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (unknown route) 1 dosage form. On 06-Nov-2021, the patient experienced DIPLOPIA (Double Vision), NERVOUS SYSTEM DISORDER (Neurological medical condition), HEAD DISCOMFORT (when she tried to hold her head up, she felt the room going around), IMPAIRED DRIVING ABILITY (could not drive a car for 5 days), DIZZINESS (She was very Dizzy) and NAUSEA (Nauseous). On an unknown date, the patient experienced VACCINATION COMPLICATION (adverse reaction to the booster shot). On 11-Nov-2021, HEAD DISCOMFORT (when she tried to hold her head up, she felt the room going around), IMPAIRED DRIVING ABILITY (could not drive a car for 5 days), DIZZINESS (She was very Dizzy) and NAUSEA (Nauseous) had resolved. At the time of the report, DIPLOPIA (Double Vision) had not resolved and NERVOUS SYSTEM DISORDER (Neurological medical condition) and VACCINATION COMPLICATION (adverse reaction to the booster shot) outcome was unknown.No treatment medications were reported. This case was linked to MOD-2021-404053, MOD-2021-404058 (Patient Link). Most recent FOLLOW-UP information incorporated above includes: On 02-Dec-2021: Added the medical history (Cataract Surgery, Diabetes, Hypothyroidism, double vision),events (Dizzy, Nauseous, Double Vision, head discomfort,  impaired driving ability, Neurological disorder NOS), Concomitant medications (Metformin 1000mg BID, Synthroid, Lantus insulin.)
HISTORY: Medical History/Concurrent Conditions: Cataract operation (Summer 2021); Double vision.

The patient's past medical history included Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma. Concurrent medical conditions included Diabetes mellitus and COVID-19 (the lingering COVID.). Her skin feels dehydrated), SKIN TIGHTNESS (skin feels tight), PAROSMIA (distorted sense of smell), TASTE DISORDER (food tasted weird [before and after Moderna booster]), MALAISE (don't feel well), PARAESTHESIA (pins and needles on my feet, like a neuropathy kind of feeling), THIRST (constantly thirsty), DIARRHOEA (diarrhea) and PAIN (body hurts) outcome was unknown and FEELING ABNORMAL (still feeling a little weird from the lingering COVID/didn't feel better/ still feel really weird) had not resolved.            Concomitant medications was not reported. Patient stated on 30-nov-2021 Tuesday last night she felt really bad and CT scan was done.she didn't feel better, so she called back the nurse hotline, who told her to go to the emergency room. On 30-Apr-2021, received second dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (unknown route) dosage was changed to 1 dosage form. On 01-Dec-2021, received third dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (unknown route) dosage was changed to 1 dosage form. On 02-Dec-2021,  after starting mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine), the patient experienced PYREXIA (Fever). On 03-Dec-2021, the patient experienced VACCINATION SITE PAIN (Arm is sore on her left). At the time of the report, VACCINATION SITE PAIN (Arm is sore on her left) outcome was unknown. SYMPTOM_TEXT: Pfizer booster shot received Wednesday AM Dec 1st.  At 3 AM Dec 2nd, awakened with vertigo. Sat up and the world turned upside down. From 3 AM through to December 6th had severe, severe vertigo side effect reaction to booster shot. At this time, i still have vertigo but it's debilitating effect has lessened enough so that I can stand and walk without a "death" grip on some sort of support.  Needed to sit quietly with head straight and not move during the day and to sleep (in a chair) with minimal moving around the home to avoid falling and to keep the vertigo from making me ill. On Friday AM vertigo caused nausea which passed.  Vertigo is getting better, BUT it is unknown IF the vertigo will remain to some degree or come back at some point. very unsettling.  IN research Vertigo and definitely not severe vertigo (not dizziness but vertigo) is NOT listed even as a rare side effect. It should be listed because I have talked to a few people and found out that I am not the only one who got this same reaction to the booster shot.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I am getting that horrible taste from the shot (Covid 19 vaccine) in my mouth; It is still there bothering me; I am tasting the horrible side effect of salt; I can't get rid of it in my mouth; It is like I am eating horrible amount of salt or I swallowed the ocean water; I feel like I am going to get sick but it doesn't go away; This is a spontaneous report received from a contactable reporter(s) (Consumer or other non HCP). The reporter is the patient.  A 80 year-old female patient received bnt162b2 (BNT162B2), administered in arm left (Lot number: EN6205) at the age of 80 years as dose 1, single for covid-19 immunisation. Relevant medical history included: "High Blood Pressure" (unspecified if ongoing). Concomitant medication(s) included: AMLODIPINE BESYLATE; TELMISARTAN; CHLORTHALIDONE. The following information was reported: DYSGEUSIA (non-serious), outcome "unknown", described as "I am getting that horrible taste from the shot (Covid 19 vaccine) in my mouth; It is still there bothering me"; DYSGEUSIA (non-serious), outcome "unknown", described as "I am tasting the horrible side effect of salt; I can't get rid of it in my mouth; It is like I am eating horrible amount of salt or I swallowed the ocean water"; MALAISE (non-serious), outcome "unknown", described as "I feel like I am going to get sick but it doesn't go away". Therapeutic measures were not taken as a result of dysgeusia, dysgeusia, malaise.  Additional information: Consumer stated, "I hope that you can give me information because I have a problem, I am 80 years old (not clarified). I did get the shot (Clarified as Pfizer-BioNTech COVID-19 Vaccine) Saturday at 3 O'clock and what I need to ask you is, could you tell me some of the chemicals or whatever that is in this drug and I will tell you why, for most of my life I have been a person, I know it sounds weird but every time I get around certain cleaning chemicals, fertilizers, gasoline or anything like that I taste it in my mouth. I have to be very careful even fertilizers that is in bags. When I got two-part shingle shot (Unspecified Shot) I even tasted that, I know this sounds weird." Consumer further stated, "So, I get the shot at 3 O'clock and within 4-5 minutes while I was sitting there, I had this horrible, horrible chemical taste in my mouth and my husband said, is something wrong with you and I said, I am getting that horrible taste from the shot (Covid 19 vaccine) in my mouth. He said, what do you want to talk, and I said no I am sure it will go away. Bilateral pulmonary embolism (PE); Shortness of breath (SOB); This spontaneous case  was retrieved on 25-Nov-2021 from Vaccine Adverse Event Reporting System (VAERS) (reference number: 1857195-1), reported by other healthcare professional and concerned a 61-year-old, female patient.   The patient's concurrent conditions included alcoholism, hypertension, hyperlipidemia, asthma and allergy to ACE inhibitors, causing cough. The patient's concomitant medications included hydrochlorothiazide and citalopram, both used for an unreported indication.   On 20-Oct-2021, the patient was vaccinated with Flucelvax Quadrivalent (influenza vaccine, subunit influenza virus vaccine polyvalent; route of administration: intramuscular, dose, anatomical location and indication: not reported). The batch number reported was 308481.  On the same day, the patient was vaccinated with non-company, co-suspect Boostrix (diphtheria vaccine toxoid, pertussis vaccine acellular 3-component, tetanus vaccine toxoid; route of administration: intramuscular, dose, anatomical location and indication: not reported). The batch number reported was MR5RK.  On 27-Oct-2021, seven days after receiving Flucelvax Quadrivalent and Boostrix, the patient experienced shortness of breath (SOB).   On 28-Oct-2021, the patient was seen in the doctor's office for SOB, had unspecified testing (labs/imaging as reported) and was admitted for bilateral pulmonary embolism (PE). Ultrasound (U/S) and echocardiogram (echo) were planned.   At the time of initial reporting, the patient had not recovered from the events.   The reporter did not provide causality assessment.  Both events were assessed as serious due to seriousness criterion of hospitalization. Additionally, the event of 'pulmonary embolism' was considered to be medically significant by a Physician within Seqirus' Pharmacovigilance and Risk Management Department.  Company comment: A 61-year-old female patient developed dyspnea and bilateral pulmonary embolism 8 days after receiving Flucelvax Quadrivalent and non-company co-suspect Boostrix vaccines. The patient's concurrent conditions included alcoholism, hypertension, hyperlipidemia and asthma. Causality for the reported events is assessed as not related due to biological implausibility.; Sender's Comments: A 61-year-old female patient developed dyspnea and bilateral pulmonary embolism 8 days after receiving Flucelvax Quadrivalent and non-company co-suspect Boostrix vaccines. I was offered and got the flu shot at my annual gynecological exam. It went fine and I had the expected sore arm, but that night I noticed my shoulder seemed more sore than usual - more in the joint that the muscle than I normally see. We were at my fianc�'s daughter's house and she's a pharmacist so I mentioned this so she looked at my arm and immediately noticed that they gave the injection too high in my shoulder. She said it could lead to some complications so keep an eye on it and have it checked out if the pain didn't go away after a week or two. It continued to be sore and even getting painful. On November 17th I finally sent a message to my doctor , telling her that it hurt every time I moved my arm and even without movement, there was a constant ache with pain shooting into my arm. I found out she was out of the office due to a family emergency and continued trying to treat it with ice, heat,  and Tylenol (I can't take ibuprofen), but it got so bad that on Friday, November 19th I finally went to urgent care. They examined me and felt it was due to the incorrect placement of the flu shot injection and resulting inflammation and prescribed me prednisone and told me to try to keep moving my arm to help the inflammation go away.  The prednisone helped while I was on it, although it didn't completely take the pain away, but as soon as I was off of the meds, the pain came right back. As urgent care told me to update Dr  if I still had pain after I was done with the prednisone, I did that. On November 29th, she prescribed another short taper of prednisone, which I just finished. This short taper slightly helped, but I still had significant pain during it, and now that I'm done with it, the pain is back at extreme levels.
LAB_DATA: Urgent care visit but no lab or medical tests

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Right after felt sick to my stomach. The next two days after I had fever type symptoms. They went away but I had a raw/burning type feeling in my lungs when I would breathe deep. This lasted and worsened until November 27/28. That night I woke up with chills that made me violently shiver, accompanied by a dull headache. That lasted until I was able to take a really hot shower and then the chills turned to sweats. The headache lasted over a week. We brought our new born baby home that day as well so I had to quarantine for the next week. The symptoms remained similar, chills and sweats back and forth with periods of feeling fine. All the while having the chest sickness getting worse. It turned into the feeling of a chest cold with difficulty breathing deep. Every deep breathe causes a coughing fit. I took a covid test November 31 with negative results. I cannot get my new born daughter sick but I don't know what this is. Again last night, December 6/7, I awoke around 3am with the chills. I tried to warm up but couldn't without taking a hot shower. After that I was too hot and had the sweats. This continuing for a month has made me want to report it and see if this is a common occurance. I haven't went to a Dr. about it because it seems like it gets better and then another night of chills and sweats.
ALLERGIES: Allergic to Penicillin. Not sure the reaction to it though.

Patient received a dose of Pfizer COVID-19 Vaccine  Peds formulation (5-11yr) that may have been reconstituted with a single use vial of 0.9%NS that was entered into multiple times to reconstitute other vials of Pfizer vaccine. Staff did not realize the 10mL vial was for single use only (to take out 1.3mL then discard). Each time the vial was used it was swabbed with alcohol and a new syringe was used to enter the vial then to add the diluent to the Pfizer vaccine for reconstitution. The 10mL, 0.9%NS vial was disposed of at the end of each day. The patient did not experience any adverse reaction. At the recommendation of Pfizer and the Agency, due to lack of stability data, it was advised to revaccinate the patient.

The upstate Medical Director, was contacted, and advised that a 12 y/o who received the second dose of vaccine as a 10 microgram pediatric dose is not required to have the dose repeated per the CDC guidance. It is not known if the child will be as protected with the slightly lower dose since that was not studied, but I don?t think giving another dose at this time would be recommended unless there were special circumstances.  If the child is immunosuppressed in the moderate to severe category, his or her guardian can talk to their doctor about it. The clients father was made aware of all of the included information.

Aside from the initial headache/achiness that I was told initially would accompany the vaccination, what has evolved since is much more concerning/grievous. Three (3) days after receiving the Janssen Johnson & Johnson Vaccine, I tried to participate in a community 5k. Being I have competed in multiple marathons, a 5K is a relatively simple task. At 1 mile I had to quit/withdraw because I was having something akin to an asthma attack and an extremely accelerated heart rate. I returned to my vehicle where I waited for my heart to return to a normal rate, but then began what can only be described as a coughing fit that lasted for close to 30 mins. Through that day and into the next, any physical exertion resulted in shortness of breath and accelerated heart rate. Example; walking up a flight of stairs. Or bending over to pick something up. Four (4) days after getting vaccinated I was walking down a ramp at a sporting event stadium, and again had something like an asthma attack, accompanied this time with significant chest pain under the right pectoral.  To date, 15 days later I cannot exert any physical effort, even something as simple as carrying in a small bag of groceries into my home without my heart accelerating and running out of breath, the way I would be formerly when sprinting to the finish of a long training run.
LAB_DATA: I've not sought medical attention for this, for fear that the cure could be even more adverse than the vaccine. I am not a medical expert but because my fiance  has asthma, I have a pretty good understanding of what asthma is or does to the body. I at this point suspect I will never again be able to run like I once had due to this damedable vaccine that the government forced on it's citizens. I WAS FINE BEFORE, AND NOW I MAY NEVER RETURN TO NORMAL.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: My first dose of Moderna was on 4/5/21. Nausea started on 4/13 around 11am, concluded in vomiting, and ended after 3 hours. On 4/14 I did not feel sick but my brain was in a fog and I couldn't think. Around 8pm that night I developed a headache. That night, around 1am on 4/15, I woke up drenched in a cold sweat with a splitting headache. The pain was so bad it caused me to vomit. I would describe the level of pain in my head as unbearable. For a while I honestly thought I might be having an aneurysm, but figured a call to 911 would not save my life it were actually an aneurysm (also when in that much pain, making a call is impossible anyway). I slept until 2pm 4/15 when the pain became bearable. I suffer tension headaches almost monthly, but this was very different and intense. It was the first migraine and only I've experienced. Early on 4/16 my period started about 1.5 weeks earlier than it should have.   Though I at first doubted this was a reaction to the vaccine, given it happened a week later, I have since realized it likely was. Sometime after my second dose, I spoke to friends, also women in their 30s, and four of them had had a similar series of events - migraine and early period - a number of days after their first dose. Medical studies really need to take women?s health into account. Knowing I might have this reaction would NOT have stopped me from getting the vaccine, but it would have made me feel a lot better during the episode to know what was happening and why, as opposed to thinking I might be dying of an aneurysm. To realize I was not alone in the experience was an immense relief.  I have not had a migraine since. I had no discernible reaction to the second dose. I have yet to notice any reaction to the booster, which I got five days ago. I wrote down symptoms back in April, and wanted to wait til after the second dose to report; I forgot to until now.
HISTORY: Endometriosis - asymptomatic except for gradual formation of cysts. Had surgical removal 8 years ago. Treated with Mirena IUD, until removal November 2020.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: A few hours after the vaccine was administered patient had severe malaise. She laid in bed for approximately 20 hours. She got up the morning after the vaccine and had a headache. She went to take Tylenol but syncopated while standing in her bathroom. She continued to experience episodes of lightheadedness and brain fog.  ECG and 3-day Holter monitor were unremarkable. Echocardiogram showed depressed ejection fraction (43%) and wall motion abnormalities. Coronary angiogram showed no coronary artery disease to explained these findings. Cardiac MRI showed improved ejection fraction and improving (although not fully normal) wall motion.  Patient has experienced an improvement in her symptoms, but not full return to normal. This episode and imaging findings are suspicious for stress induced (Takotsubo) cardiomyopathy. Patient will get a repeat echocardiogram in 3 months to ensure resolution of wall motion abnormalities.
LAB_DATA: ECG 10/13/21- sinus bradycardia at a rate of 50 bpm; 3 Day Holter 11/11/2021; 1. The patient's baseline rhythm during the monitoring period was normal sinus rhythm; 2. Heart rate varied from 38 bpm to 101 bpm. The patient?s average heart rate was 61 bpm; 3. Holter monitor analyzed duration was for 3 days 1 hours; 4. The patient had 0.02% ventricular ectopic activity (56 total beats) in the form of 56 isolated PVCs; 5. The patient had 0.07% supraventricular ectopy in the form of 193 singlets; 6. Other evidence of heart block or arrhythmia: None; 7. Patient diary: No reported events; Transthoracic echocardiogram 11/19/2021; The mid/distal septum, anterior, apical, and distal lateral walls are akinetic. Left ventricular systolic function is mildly decreased. The quantitative EF by 2D Simpson biplane is 43%; Right ventricular systolic function is normal; There is mild aortic regurgitation; There is no previous study for comparison in our system; Coronary angiogram 11/24/2021; Left Main; Large caliber vessel that birfucates into a left anterior descending and left circumflex artery. The left main is free of any angiographically significant coronary artery disease; Left Anterior Descending; There is a large-caliber vessel that coursed along the anterior interventricular groove and tapers as it reaches to the apex. The LAD gives off 1 large caliber diagonal branch in its proximal portion and a series of small caliber diagonal branches.  In the mid LAD there is approximately 30 mm segment of myocardial bridging. There are mild luminal irregularities in the LAD however there is no angiographically significant coronary artery disease; Left Circumflex; Large-caliber nondominant vessel that gives off a large caliber obtuse marginal branch.  The left circumflex system is free of any angiographically significant coronary artery disease; Right Coronary Artery; Large-caliber dominant vessel that gives off a PDA and PL branch. The RCA system is free of any angiographically significant coronary artery disease; CMR 12/4/2021; Preserved biventricular resting systolic function. LVEF 64%, RVEF 62%; There is mild hypokinesis of the left ventricular apex, with no abnormal late gadolinium enhancement to suggest inflammation, infiltration or scarring. In the appropriate clinical setting, findings could represent (recovering) Takotsubo cardiomyopathy.
OTHER_MEDS: cholecalciferol; levothyroxine; metoprolol succinate; rosuvastatin; omega 3; multivitamin; vitamin K
PRIOR_VAX: Patient had similar profound malaise after her second covid vaccine but no syncope

Tested positive for COVID-19 several days ago and she was symptomatic approximately 3 days ago.  Patient describes moderate URI-like symptoms with runny nose sore throat generalized body aches.  Patient was concerned about the nausea and wanted to come to the ER to be evaluated.  No history of intra-abdominal surgeries.  Her nausea has had minimal at this time and also her abdominal pain is at a minimal at this time.  REVIEW OF SYSTEMS:     General: Denies unusual wt loss/gain Eyes: Denies pain or photophobia. Denies vaginal discharge, bleeding or pregnancy. Neuro: No reported syncope, dizziness, or any focal numbness or weakness. Denies headaches or stiff neck. MS: Denies any back, neck or extremity pain. Also denies any abnormal swelling. Skin: No itching, rashes, or unusual sweating.       Remainder of systems reviewed and are negative.
EXTREME LEFT SHOULDER PAIN PERSISTING 60 DAYS.   TWO TRIPS TO URGENT CARE AND PHYSICAL THERAPY.
LAB_DATA: X-RAY LEFT SHOULDER 11-15-2021   ALLERGIES: HE HAS NO KNOWN ALLERGIES.    THE PATIENT RECEIVED THE 2ND OF THE 2 SHINGRIX SERIES ON OCTOBER 28TH, AND VERY SOON THEREAFTER DEVELOPED ANTEROLATERAL SHOULDER PAIN WHICH HAS PERSISTED WITHOUT RADICULOPATHIC SOUNDING SYMPTOMS, BUT SYMPTOMATIC IN THE SENSE THAT IT HAS BOTHERED HIM TO FORWARD FLEX HIS SHOULDER MUCH ABOVE 90-100 DEGREES.  WAS SEEN IN TEC ON 11/03 AND THE DICTATION FROM THAT ENCOUNTER IS REVIEWED. SYMPTOMATIC MEASURES WERE DISCUSSED BASICALLY USING IBUPROFEN AND ACETAMINOPHEN.  THE PATIENT WAS SEEN AGAIN IN TEC ON 11/15 WITH CONTINUED SYMPTOMS LEADING TO AN X-RAY OF THE RIGHT SHOULDER, WHICH WAS READ AS SHOWING DEGENERATIVE CHANGES, THOUGH THESE ARE FAIRLY MINIMAL AS I LOOK AT THE FILMS AND WE LOOKED AT THEM TOGETHER TODAY WHICH HAS GENERALLY GOOD GLENOHUMERAL SPACE MAINTENANCE.    PATIENT IS RIGHT-HANDED AND BECAUSE OF HIS DISCOMFORT BEYOND ABOUT 90-100 DEGREES OF FORWARD FLEXION, HE HAS BEEN FAVORING THE SHOULDER, AND UNDERSTANDABLY SO THAT WE TALKED ABOUT THE IMPORTANCE OF TRYING TO MAINTAIN RANGE OF MOTION IN AN INJURED SHOULDER REGION SO AS TO AVOID CONTRACTED MUSCLES, LIGAMENTS/ROTATOR CUFF STRUCTURES, ETC., AND HE RECOGNIZED THAT PRINCIPAL RIGHT AWAY AND AS I EVALUATE HIS RANGE OF MOTION ABDUCTION, INTERNAL AND EXTERNAL ROTATION GENERALLY WELL PERFORMED.  HE HAS SOME LIMITATION OF INTERNAL ROTATION, BUT THE MAIN DISCOMFORT IS ANTEROLATERALLY WITH A FORWARD FLEXION AS MENTIONED.  THERE IS NO MASS IN THE REGION.  NO EVIDENCE OF INFLAMMATION.   ASSESSMENT: There apparently was some type of inflammation that developed after the most recent Shingrix immunization (the 1st Shingrix given in August I believe did not cause him any symptoms at all, and I suspect that his recent symptoms will improve, noting that he is scheduled to be seen in physical therapy on 12/02/2021.  I spoke with him about a symptom limited progressive exercise program, focusing on 25 reps twice daily with all of the above ranges of motion:  Most importantly forward flexion and then abduction, internal rotation, external rotation in a progressive manner as his symptoms would allow.  I suggested we could try a short course of steroids for its anti-inflammatory effect, but he did not wish to do that, preferring to continue with his ibuprofen and acetaminophen regimen-he could possibly consider locally applied over-the-counter Voltaren 1% gel as well for its local anti-inflammatory effect.  We talked about the potential side effects of nonsteroidal products which should always be used with food noting that his most recent serum creatinine on 03/15/21 was 0.94 with a GFR of 79.    Again, the concept of progressive range-of-motion symptom limited is quite important so as to hopefully avoid loss of function, the extreme of which would be a "frozen shoulder" but conceptually I think was useful to him in terms of trying to be more active with his dominant right shoulder.  He also will receive the high-dose influenza vaccine today and a booster for his Pfizer 1 of which will be given in the right shoulder.  The other the left shoulder. He can decide which of the 2 he prefers.    As mentioned, he is scheduled to be seen in physical therapy on 12/02/2021-I did not reschedule him in this department at this time, but he is urged to be in touch should he have subsequent signs/symptoms of concern despite today's discussion and recommendations.   IMPRESSION: Apparent post immunization rotator cuff inflammation, right shoulder as discussed above. 11/22/2021 18:15 DT: 11/22/2021 23:21 DOC#: 938874862 MT: im

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I got the booster vaccine (my third Pfizer) 12/4/21 around 10:30am and was fine until the sore arm started that evening around dinner.  I woke up around 12:30am 12/5/21 with fever, chills/sweating, my entire body was sore, intense migraine, heartburn, and for a short period that night a rapid heartbeat.  I ate some tums and continued drinking water and gatorade, and took ibuprofen Sunday morning to help.  Muscle soreness, migraine, fever, and body aches were almost all gone by Sunday evening.  Monday morning, 12/5, I woke up with what looks like a viral rash on my chest/stomach/back.  I still have that now but it doesn't seem to be spreading or getting worse (maybe a little better at this point but marginally, if at all).  I have a doctor's appointment scheduled for a physical in January at a new primary care doctor closer to where I live, but no symptoms at this time seem serious enough for me to go to an urgent care.  I had only a sore arm and migraine after shot 1.  After shot 2 I had a migraine, body aches, and a fever which resolved in under 2 days.  This is the first time I've gotten the rash and the rapid heart rate.
CUR_ILL: Minor stomach bug for about 24 hours that resolved day prior, sore throat with congestion that lasted about a week prior to Thanksgiving.
ALLERGIES: Sulfa drugs, penicillin, salicylic acid, bees, nickel.
